Retreat to the main bedroom which offers a private exit and dual vanity sinks with a oversized walk in closet. You will love all the storage space this home has to offers, private large laundry area with additional storage just off the garage. Newly installed carpet and tile and bedrooms offer custom wood shutters. Backyard Oasis with you're own sparkly private Pool and Jacuzzi and a large grassy area for entertaining with a covered patio. Side yard also has additional parking with a RV gate. No stone left unturned with this remodel, shows light and bright and is in pristine condition.

column9: Where history meets modern city livingwelcome to Orpheum Lofts!Setting the stage in Downtown Phoenix's only pre-war Art Deco condo building, this 1-bedroom, 1-bath residence blends the soul of a bygone era with the pulse of the city. Step through the show-stopping lobby and you'll feel transported to a classic New York buildingthere's truly nothing else like it in Phoenix. Residents enjoy access to a fitness center, indoor pool, community lounge, and a peaceful outdoor courtyard. Just outside your door: the Orpheum Theatre, sports arenas, and a vibrant mix of restaurants, cocktail bars, and nightlife. Whether you're searching for a full-time home or a stylish city pied--terre, Orpheum Lofts delivers an unmatched downtown lifestyle. Parking available!

column9: The residence at artHAUS offers one of the only two distinctive floor plans. It features a split layout encompassing 1, 275 sqft, 2 bedrooms/2 bathrooms, an open-concept design with high ceilings & abundant natural light. This unit comes with two parking spaces in a secured and enclosed parking garage, with one of the spaces equipped with a universal EV charger. Furthermore, the owner has implemented several elegant customizations to the unit, including the custom-designed staircase, the upgraded closet design & lighting system, a spacious kitchen island, backsplash, under-cabinetry lighting, upgraded toilets, & ceiling fans. artHAUS comprises 25 urban dwellings designed and developed by Jason Boyer, the recipient of the 2017 Builder's Choice & Custom Home Design Award Conveniently situated within walking distance of popular attractions such as the Phoenix Art Museum, Hance Park, and the ASU Downtown Campus, as well as some of the finest dining options in Phoenix, artHAUS prioritizes sustainability and energy efficiency. All units meet stringent Energy Star and LEED for Homes certification criteria. The building has a rooftop solar array that offsets 100% of the HOA power demand and enclosed parking garage facilities with electric vehicle charging stations available to residents.

column9: Willo Historic District home with guest housethis charming and versatile property could be yours! A welcoming covered patio leads into a 1, 497 SF main home featuring two spacious primary suites, 2.5 bathrooms, a formal living room with a gas fireplace, and distinct yet open living and dining areas. The 290 SF guest house includes a private bathroom, full kitchen (fridge + stove/oven), ample storage, private patio, and its own entry gateideal for multi-generational living, guests, or rental income (short- or long-term). The backyard is an entertainer's dream with mature trees, low-maintenance turf, stylish patio with shade sails, bistro lights, and an outdoor fireplace. Rear carport for two cars with motorized gate and EV charger included. W/ two on-site parking spots in front! Willo is a vibrant Historic District which offers KIDS Club, Monthly Community Happy Hours, a highly attended Historic Home Tour. Historic homes can qualify for property tax breaks if owner occupied and meets Historic Preservation Office requirements. Located in the heart of the City but feels like a community - close to light rail, minutes to walk or bike downtown, easy freeway access and close to some of the best hospitals in Central Phoenix!

column9: NEW ROOF!! Charming Roosevelt Historic District Home with Casita. Welcome to this stunning 4-bedroom, 3-bathroom residence nestled in the heart of the Roosevelt Historic District. This delightful home combines modern amenities with timeless character, making it a perfect retreat! Step inside to discover a spacious parlor area that exudes warmth and charm, featuring original built-ins and beautiful stained glass windows that bathe the space in colorful light. The open layout seamlessly connects the living areas, perfect for both entertaining and everyday living. The main floor primary bedroom offers a private sanctuary with French doors leading to a serene patio, complete with a hot tuban ideal spot for relaxation and unwinding after a long day. With three additional well-appointed bedrooms, there's plenty of room for all. An inviting upstairs study provides a peaceful work or flex space, while the newly installed AC unit ensures comfort year-round. The separate casita adds versatility, making it perfect for guests, a home office, or an art studio. Enjoy the vibrant lifestyle of the Roosevelt Historic District, with its unique blend of culture, dining, and community events. Don't miss the opportunity to make this enchanting home yours!

Built in 1997, this residence offers the rare opportunity to enjoy newer systems and an open-concept floor planall while surrounded by the character and charm of early 20th-century architecture. The curb appeal fits with Willo's tree-lined streets and vintage homes, yet the interior tells a more modern story: vaulted ceilings, generous natural light, and a layout designed for how we live today. The kitchen offers updated finishes, generous storage, and an island that opens to the living area. The primary suite includes a walk-in closet and en-suite bath. Bonus, a 2 car garage! All this just steps from local shops, restaurants, and museumsyour Willo lifestyle is waiting!

Conveniently located near top dining, entertainment, and cultural attractions, this property is ideal for those seeking a dynamic city lifestyle.

column9: Welcome to Willo! This charming red-brick home with two-car garage boasts historic integrity with plaster walls, crown molding, wood floors and well-preserved mid-century bathroom tile. The home has undergone updates over the years including a new roof, new HVAC, updated plumbing, electrical, shutters and a heated pool. Enjoy gatherings in the huge living room or formal dining room, then swing open the butler's door to the kitchen with newer cabinetry, a unique 'pop-up' eat-in kitchen nook and back door leading to an outdoor dining area. This home offers a flexible floor plan with 3 spacious bedrooms and a bonus room with exterior access that can be used as an office, studio or a large laundry room. Schedule an appointment, today!

column9: Welcome! Live where past & future meet across from a park, tucked between exciting Downtown PHX and famous Roosevelt Historic District. HOA fee is $350/mo, lowest in the area!A spacious floor plan offers 2-car garage, 336 SF 1st floor flex space, living and family rooms, 4 balconies, 2 en suite bedrooms & full-size laundry. This townhome blends character with today's comforts. Finishes like real wood flooring, cabinetry and doors add authenticity, and LED lighting, updated fixtures & gas fireplace create a modern ambiance. Community recently painted with new exterior lighting and signage. Your dog will love Portland Park, Hance Park/dog park and tree-lined streets. Enjoy being moments from a vibrant mix of arts, restaurants & coffee, museums & entertainment while living with privacy. Home Features & Finishes This three-level townhome seamlessly blends historic character with modern design. Natural wood flooring, solid wood doors, and cabinetry add warmth and depth, while LED recessed lighting, stylish fixtures, and fans create an inviting ambiance. The kitchen boasts a breakfast bar, gas range, and pantry, opening to spacious living and family room areas with two covered balconies. The gas fireplace adds charm, and blinds throughout ensure privacy. Upstairs, both en suite bedrooms include walk-in closets, private balconies, and a full-size laundry room, while the primary bathroom features a dual vanity, soaking tub, and separate shower. A two-car garage and a 336 SF first-floor flex space with a closet and half bath make this home ideal for a home office or studio. Downtown Location & Nearby Attractions This prime location at Portland Square Townhomes places you in the heart of Downtown Phoenix's thriving arts, cultural and entertainment district, yet at the perfect corner for peace and privacy. Portland Park is at your doorstep, with Hance Park, its playgrounds, dog park, and Japanese Friendship Garden just minutes away. Roosevelt Historic District, with its stunning homes and buildings dating back to 1895, surrounds you, offering a unique blend of architectural beauty and urban energy. Experience Phoenix's thriving arts and culture scene just minutes from your door. Immerse yourself in First Fridays, the city's iconic monthly art walk showcasing local talent, galleries, and live performances. Explore world-class institutions like the Phoenix Art Museum and the Heard Museum, both offering renowned exhibitions and cultural experiences. The nearby Children's Museum of Phoenix, Arizona Science Center, and Heritage Square add to the city's rich tapestry of creativity and history, making this location a dynamic hub for art lovers and urban explorers alike. Dining, coffee, and nightlife are right outside your door. Within two blocks, you'll find FEZ, Saint Pasta, Rough Rider, Valley Coffee Company, GenuWine Arizona, Matt's Big Breakfast, The Churchill, Snooze, The Grand, The Vig, Starbucks, and more. First & Last, Pita Jungle, SoSoBa Ramen, Lola Coffee, Salon RO5, and a dry cleaner are just next door. When guests visit, The FOUND:RE Hotel is nearby, offering a stylish place to stay, complete with MATCH restaurant. Take advantage of their pool day pass! Portland Square Townhomes & Historic Community Built in 2002, Portland Square Townhomes offer a unique opportunity to experience downtown living with a connection to Phoenix's historic roots. This intimate community of just ten homes has recently been refreshed with a new exterior paint and color scheme, updated lighting, and modern signage, enhancing both its curb appeal and connection to the surrounding architectural heritage. Situated at 3rd Avenue & Portland Street, this community is adjacent to the Roosevelt Historic District and within reach of 15 of Phoenix's most celebrated historic neighborhoods, where homes and buildings from 1895 to 1930 stand as a testament to the city's rich past. Yet, this home is also positioned at the edge of a thriving, forward-moving urban corewhere

column9: Urban Elegance in the Heart of Phoenix: Discover the epitome of urban downtown living in this prestigious MOVE-IN-READY 2-Bedroom, 1-Bath loft, within the historic Orpheum Lofts Art Deco building that seamlessly combines timeless elegance with modern amenities. This unit offers an exquisite blend of classic charm and contemporary comfort. The open-concept design showcases red-brick walls and exposed ductwork, and a stunning wall of windows overlooking the courtyard, providing a stylish industrial edge that's as unique as it is inviting. A full kitchen with a complete appliance package and the convenience of a washer and dryer in-unit ensures that your daily life flows with ease. Built in 1931 as office space and completely renovated in 2005 into this fabulous residential community, this historic building stands as a testament to Phoenix's rich heritage, offering a timeless atmosphere that is truly one-of-a-kind. This unit provides an elegant interior and is privy to a suite of top-tier amenities. Enjoy the luxury of a heated pool and spa, a sauna and steam room, additional storage, and a well-equipped fitness center. The spacious clubroom and office center make remote work and meetings a breeze, and a 24-hour doorman adds an extra layer of security and convenience. Location is everything, and this loft's prime spot puts you within walking distance of some of Phoenix's most beloved attractions. The Orpheum Lofts is just steps away from exquisite entertainment, culinary delights, sporting venues, grand theaters, and the ever popular Roosevelt Row making it easy to enjoy the vibrant cultural and sporting scene that the city offers. If you're seeking a residence that blends historic charm, contemporary comfort, and unbeatable location, this Orpheum Lofts 2-bedroom loft is the perfect choice. Don't miss the chance to call this unique and inviting space your home. Make an offer today!

column9: Urban Vibes Meet Historic Charm - Your Downtown Oasis Awaits! Live in the heart of the action while tucked away in your own secure, stylish sanctuary. This rare gem of a unit boasts jaw-dropping views of both downtown and uptown, with an industrial-chic vibe thanks to exposed concrete floors and ductwork. Cook like a pro in the stainless steel kitchen, unwind in a fully remodeled bathroom, and soak in the skyline from every angle. Once a mid-century hotel, this historic mid-rise has been transformed into a boutique urban retreat, offering a full suite of modern amenities: resort-style pool with umbrellas and ample patio seating (perfect for summer soires!), a state-of-the-art fitness center with sweeping views, a chic residents' lounge and entertainment space with full kitchen, restrooms, and even an elevator for added convenience. Covered, secure parking? Check. HOA that covers water, HVAC, and electric? Double check. All that's missing is you. Steps from Phoenix's cultural pulsewalk to Roosevelt Row, the Phoenix Art Gallery, speakeasies, microbreweries, bistros, and Light Rail. Catch a game at Chase Field or The Footprint Center and be home before the crowds clear. These coveted units rarely hit the marketand when they do, they don't last. Come claim your corner of the skyline before someone else does.

column9: Experience urban luxury at Portland on the Park in downtown Phoenix with the perfect blend of city life & modern convenience. This stunning 1 BR 1 BA 891 sq ft 3rd Floor Condo offers a contemporary design, open concept, floor to ceiling windows w/peaceful views & tons of natural light. The modern kitchen boasts quartz countertops, sleek cabinetry, island, & SS appliances w/gas cooktop. The adjacent great room's expansive windows & unique corner patio overlook the lush greenery, koi ponds, walking paths, & waterfalls of the Japanese Friendship Garden. Spacious executive primary BR with north facing views, walk-in closet, extensive cabinet enclosures, ensuite bath w/dual sinks & elegant walk-in shower. Building amenities are first class & include state-of-the-art rooftop lounge w/panoramic breathtaking views of the city, Camelback & Piestewa Mountains, the Japanese Friendship Garden & Hance Park to the north & expansive cityscape & South Mountain views to the south with the tree-lined Portland St in front. The heated pool, fitness center, welcoming lobby, 24-hr concierge, gas BBQ grills, fire pit, multiple TVs, & 7th Floor outdoor patio lounge add additional amenities. Close to light rail, coffee & wine bars, restaurants, museums, dog park, sporting events, & the airport. This condo is a perfect home, executive flat, or short-term rental (31+ days or longer).

column9: Rare two-bedroom home at historic Orpheum Lofts, the only full-service, pre-war condominium in Phoenix! 807 features one of the rarest floorplans in the building, offering two bedrooms and 1.5 bathrooms within an efficient layout and no wasted space. 10'8'' ceilings with concrete beams and exposed brick walls. Recently renovated with new wood floors and an electric fireplace in the 2nd bedroom. Orpheum Lofts was originally built in 1931 as the Title and Trust building. Today, it's a full-service residential building with key-locked elevators, attended lobby, outdoor terrace, gym, and pool. Storage units available. Walking distance to the light rail, Wren & Wolf, Footprint Center, & more! Can be purchased with 808 next door to create a 3, 300+ square foot mega-loft.

Dog-friendly and close to light rail, Hance Park, dining, and more!

column9: Welcome to Tapestry On Central, where luxury meets convenience in this rare single-level floor plan! This expansive residence features new fresh paint that complements the bright and airy ambiance throughout. Rarely available on the market, this home includes two spacious primary suites and a sizable den that can easily serve as a third bedroom, offering the perfect blend of comfort and functionality. Plus, it stands out as one of the best-priced per square foot condos in Midtown Phoenix! The thoughtfully designed split floor plan provides private retreats, complete with walk-in closets, extra-large soaking tubs, and double vanity sinks in each full bathroom. Step out onto your large balcony and soak in the breathtaking views of Uptown Phoenix and the historic Willo district ...perfect for enjoying city lights and sunsets from your north-facing vantage point. The additional powder room off the living area adds convenience for guests. The heart of the home, a grand open kitchen, boasts stunning granite countertops, a huge island, and ample cabinetry, ideal for culinary enthusiasts and entertaining guests. Recent updates, including newer engineered hardwood flooring, fresh carpet, paint, and a cozy gas fireplace, enhance the charm and appeal of this unit. An extra-large laundry and utility room provides abundant storage space, making organization a breeze. Located in a vibrant neighborhood, Tapestry On Central is close to local theaters, art galleries, and live music venues, as well as major sports venues where you can cheer on your favorite teams. Additional highlights include two premium underground parking spaces, secured entry, a heated community pool and spa, a well-equipped workout facility, and a welcoming clubhouse. With a Walgreens pharmacy and a nail salon conveniently located at Tapestry, you have everything you need just steps away from your door.

column9: Located in the heart of the Roosevelt Historic District, this beautifully restored 1912 craftsman bungalow offers a rare opportunity to own a piece of Phoenix history. Commonly referred to as the Austin Winfield Morrill House, the charm of this home has never left! Thoughtfully updated to blend original designs with modern convenience, this home is a perfect balance of past and present. You'll even have one of Phoenix's last, if not the last, original hitching posts streetside, for your horse and carriage! A grand front porch welcomes you into a space rich with historic character. Inside, original details such as leaded glass windows, custom built-ins, and mouldings preserve the home's timeless appeal. The parlor and formal dining room feature stunning period woodwork, ... beamed ceilings, and a fireplace framed by leaded glass. The expanded kitchen is designed for both beauty and function, boasting a Viking 48 six-burner stove with double ovens, porcelain polished countertops, Sub-Zero refrigerator/freezer and custom cabinetry. Newly installed maple hardwood floors flow throughout, enhancing the home's warm and inviting atmosphere. Upstairs, a sunlit family room with vaulted 16-foot ceilings provides a spacious retreat. Two expansive primary suites each offer custom tile baths, walk-in closets, and access to private balconies. From these north and south balconies, breathtaking views of Downtown and Uptown Phoenix create a stunning backdrop. The lush backyard is a private oasis, complete with a deck, and mature landscapingideal for relaxing or entertaining. Significant upgrades through the years, including new plumbing, an updated electrical panel with underground utilities, HVAC systems, and sewer line, ensure modern comfort and peace of mind. This rare historic home offers exceptional character, space, and contemporary amenities in one of Phoenix's most sought-after neighborhoods. Don't miss the chance to own a beautifully preserved piece of the city of Phoenix's history!

column9: This Spanish Revival in Willo blends historic character with modern comfort. The main house features 3 beds, 2 baths, a barrel vaulted ceiling, exposed adobe, and a stunning Chicago-style window that floods the living room with natural light. The recently renovated primary suite includes a full bathroom with dual sinks and walk-in closet. Multiple outdoor living areas and a private pool are framed by lush, green landscaping that feels worlds away from desert minimalism. The detached guest house includes a kitchenette, closet, and full bathideal for guests, multi-generational living, or rental income. Located in one of the friendliest, most walkable and bikeable neighborhoods in Midtown Phoenix, just minutes from coffee shops, restaurants, light rail, hospitals, and easy freeway access.

column9: In the heart of the Willow Historic District, this 1930's home was professionally transformed in 2008. Nicely situated on an oversized 12k lot. Great 4br/3ba floorplan, living room w/original wood fireplace, solid oak flooring, Sierra Pacific wood windows, doors & custom barn doors. Gourmet kitchen features Viking appliances, custom cabinetry, Caeser stone countertops & 8ft island with butcher block counter. Primary bedroom has concrete floors, custom built in closet & french doors to the back yard. Accordian doors in great room, 500+sqft patio with Trex decking, gas fire pit, and built in BBQ. Pebble tec lap pool, outdoor shower, detached air conditioned 650sqft garage w/attic storage, attached shed & more!

column9: Experience the lifestyle of Historic PHX. Walk or bike to the best eateries, coffee shops, museums, Hance Park, music venues, and sports arenas! This charming 1920s Craftsman bungalow offers ample space for entertaining, a deep diving pool, and a wonderful floorplan to make memories. Featuring classic Craftsman details, including a welcoming red brick front porch, wood-trimmed windows, a fireplace, original stove, floor-to-ceiling glass windows, and a renovated kitchen with plenty of storage. This historic gem seamlessly blends old-world charm with contemporary updates, creating a comfortable, character-filled living space in a prime location. This truly is the best spot on one of Phoenix's most walkable and neighborly streets. Lucky you!! Seller is giving 5k for carpet of your choice.

Great walkable neighborhood close to multiple restaurants, Phoenix Theatre, Phoenix Art and the Heard Museum. One of Willo's finest streets

Wonderful Willo location within walking distance to everything in Midtown. WELCOME HOME!

column9: Home is Priced below appraisal value. Appraisal available upon request. Absolutely stunning remodeled historic bungalow in the central Phoenix Willo District now offers 3 bedrooms & 2 baths in just under 1500 SqFt with an open floor plan, vaulted ceilings, and wood floors. The remodeled kitchen features all-new shaker soft-close cabinets, Quartz countertops, tiled backsplash in a modern herringbone pattern, stainless appliances including a Forno gas range, ultra-quiet Bosch dishwasher, and drawer microwave; farmhouse sink, and large island with breakfast bar and additional storage. The primary bedroom has a walk-in closet, and a barn door provides privacy for the en-suite bath complete with dual vessel sink vanity, soaking tub, and oversized walk-in shower. Two secondary bedrooms share the hall bath which has a tiled tub/shower combo. The park-like backyard was designed for entertaining with an extensive patio, built-in BBQ island, gas firepit, Koi pond, grass for kids and pets to play on, mature shade trees, block fencing, an electric gate and a detached 1.5 car garage. Great location close to downtown Phoenix for fine dining, shopping, sports events, and much more! Don't miss this great opportunity to own in the high-demand Willo District!

column9: This great 1686 SF Cityhome is in a prime interior courtyard location in Tapestry. The nicely upgraded 2 bedroom, 2.5 Bath + den has all the expected upgrades, including SS appliances, vinyl flooring, gas stove, granite counters and new AC & window treatments. The spacious great room and den has a gas fireplace surrounded with windows and flows nicely out to the patio. Original owner, 2nd home and well cared for. This townhome has 2 parking spaces in the gated underground garage. Tapestry has a heated pool & spa and great workout facility. There is a small post office & shops there and all is steps away from the Light Rail, Heard Museum and restaurants. Very nice downtown Phoenix location and close to Sky Harbor Airport.

column9: WELCOME TO WILLO! This custom home blends in perfectly with it's historic surroundings while offering luxurious amenities unlike any other home in Willo. Perfectly located on a huge private lot, you'll be greeted by beautiful curb appeal, modern landscaping and a stunning courtyard entry. As you enter, you'll be amazed by the floor to ceiling 16' sliding glass door that opens to the resort style backyard & seamlessly blends indoor and outdoor living. A fantastic open concept floor plan showcases a gourmet kitchen & grand living spaces. The home offers an incredible primary suite with a gorgeous bathroom featuring designer fixtures, finishes, and heated floors which connects directly to the closet of your dreams. The home also offers a fantastic lock-off guest suite complete with it's own bathroom and kitchenette that's perfect for visitors. Designer details have been added throughout the home to highlight it's soaring ceilings and beautiful customizations. Outside you'll enjoy an incredible pool, amazing patio spaces and an oversized two car garage that's temperature controlled. Enjoy living in a neighborhood that feels like a small town in the city, within a home that feels like a luxury resort. Welcome Home To 59 W Cypress Street!

column9: WELCOME TO WILLO! The Hawthorne House is an incredible example of Tudor Revival architecture with its striking double gabled high pitch roof and classic porte cochere. Inside you'll be greeted by beautiful hardwood floors, timeless archways, and soaring ceilings. The living room offers a stunning barrel vaulted living room that opens to a coved dining room ceiling. The kitchen, family room and primary bedroom all offer vaulted ceilings that make the interior of this home feel like an architectural masterpiece. The primary suite offers a second fireplace, a huge walk-in closet, and a one of a kind upstairs loft. This 3 bed/2 bath main house also offers a charming detached 1 bed/1 bath guest house and a one car garage too! Outside the yard provides great patio spaces that are perfect for outdoor living and entertaining! Amazing location and walking distance to everything in Midtown. Own a piece of history - Welcome Home!

column9: One of the premier homes in popular Willo Historic District! Custom built in 2000 as a Craftsman Bungalow on spectacular double lot. Main house with 3, 100' 3br/ 3.5ba with great open floorplan and soaring 10' flat ceilings. Gorgeous wood floors t/o and double hung wood windows and 3 sets of French doors. Gourmet kitchen w/ 48'' gas range, built-in refrigerator, walk-in pantry and L-shaped island with seating for 8. Great room w/ stone covered gas fireplace and dining area overlooks amazing backyard. Game room w/ bar area, beverage and wine fridges. Spacious primary suite w/ French doors to back & custom walk-in closet. Downstairs with great TV/family room, 1 bedroom and full bath. Detached casita w/ full bath. Backyard is entertainer's paradise with lap pool, large gazebo w/ stone fireplace and outdoor kitchen w/ stainless built-in BBQ, sink and bar area. Plus a 600+ ft detached 2CG w/ cabinets & custom gated side entrance. All within walking distance to light rail, restaurants and all that midtown has to offer!

column9: This truly one of a kind loft/ brownstone offers a sophisticated and large-scale lifestyle unlike any other urban home in the Valley. Featured on the cover of Phoenix Home & Garden magazine, this home has striking design elements, including exposed materialsconcrete floors, red brick walls, exposed duct work and steel and copper accents. The open-concept kitchen and great room is perched on the top of home with exceptional city and distant mountain views. The kitchen features a large Wolf gas range, open shelves and a generous island. This space opens to the living room and extraordinary outdoor living space, making it perfect for family gatherings and entertaining with guests. The primary suite, occupying an entire floor, is a private city sanctuary complete with a large bathroom and closets. Multiple outdoor patios overlooking a lush park filled with grass and trees, provide a fresh connection with nature in the middle of the city. With 4 ensuite bedrooms and over 5400 sf of living space, this home is as functional as it is stylish. A dedicated home office meets today's needs, while a versatile craft and project room and adjacent family room, make it a perfect choice for families. A large commercial elevator serves all 5 floors of the home and the private attached garage provides direct access into the home. Located in the heart of the Phoenix Arts district just across the street from the Phoenix Art Museum, the Phoenix Theater and the Heard Museum, this exceptional property also offers proximity to dining, shopping, and other cultural hotspots, all while being tucked away in the exclusive tranquility of Chateaux on Central. This is an exceptionally special home ready for its next exceptional owners.

column9: Step into this beautifully restored 1915 Craftsman-style bungalow, seamlessly modernized in 2019 with a fully permitted remodel. Situated on nearly 1/3 of an acre - one of the largest in the Willo Historic District, this property offers incredible potential to further enhance its value whether by adding a garage, guest house, pool or all three. Don't miss this rare opportunity to own a piece of history with all the modern upgrades you desire! Offering 5 bedrooms, 3.5 bathrooms, and 2, 490 sq. ft. of living space under one roof, with designer touches throughout. The dual primary suites each feature spa-like ensuite bathrooms and expansive walk-in closets, perfect for multi-generational living. At the heart of the home, the open concept living and dining features vaulted ceilings, patio access and a true chef's dream kitchen, boasting Thermador and Bosch appliances, a full-size wine fridge, and an oversized island perfect for gatherings. Two spacious living areas create a versatile layout, ideal for both intimate and large-scale entertaining. Every detail has been thoughtfully updated, including new sewer and water main lines, HVAC with warranty, upgraded electrical and panel, and insulated ductworkensuring both character and convenience. All furnishings may be sold with a separate bill of sale.

column9: UNICORN ALERT! Rarely does this floor plan come available and it is easy to understand why! Perched on the 9th floor as an end cap unit with no shared walls giving you views South/North and sunset's from your balcony looking over the downtown skyline! Inside you will find the perfect floor plan, split bedrooms with large walk in closets and stylish bathrooms. The island kitchen overlooks the large loving room with floor to ceiling windows. Bosh appliances, quartz counters and laminate wood floors accent this unit beautifully. Best part of this plan is the extra 1/2 bath! The community boasts rooftop BBQ, fire pits, grass and amazing views. Don't miss the gym. pool. dog washing station, local art and more. Walk to everything including the parks and light rail! You will love it here!

Great upgrades and interior details throughout. This is a fantastic 3 bed/1 bath main house with a BASEMENT offering a family room and laundry! Plus a HUGE 1 bed/1bath complete guest house in the backyard too! As you step outside, the curated desert landscaping surrounds the large outdoor living spaces beautifully, and a sparkling pool makes this backyard feel like an oasis. Walking distance to everything in Midtown - WELCOME HOME!

column9: Step into a piece of history with this meticulously remodeled 1941 home nestled in the highly sought-after Willo Historic District. This residence perfectly blends timeless charm with contemporary elegance while honoring its rich heritage. The heart of this home is the expansive, fully remodeled, open kitchen and two living areas, designed for both family gatherings and entertaining guests. The chef's kitchen is a true showstopper, featuring custom walnut cabinetry, a large kitchen island with soapstone countertops, custom tile work and a separate beverage fridge. Culinary enthusiasts will appreciate the premium Bertazzoni gas range. The primary suite is fantastic with its elegantly appointed bath, double sinks, large shower and large walk-in closet and doors to the outdoor living room. The split floorplan with three additional bedrooms and 2 more baths offers flexibility for a growing family, home office, or guest quarters. The home's bathrooms have all been completely remodeled with modern touches, blending style and functionality. The outdoor living room is perfect for al fresco dining, morning coffee, or evening cocktails in front of the TV and outdoor fireplace. Enjoy peace of mind with all new plumbing, electrical, windows, roof and sewer line. This home truly offers the best of both worlds: the character and craftsmanship of the past with the convenience and style of today. Willo Historic District is renowned for its annual home tour, where residents open their doors to showcase the neighborhood's unique architectural styles. Living here means becoming part of a tight-knit community that values preservation and pride of ownership.

column9: Discover urban sophistication & breathtaking mountain, park & city light views in this stunning centrally located luxury condo on the north facing 9th floor (Club Residence) in the highly desired Portland on The Park. Seller invested nearly $100, 000 in premium upgrades after purchase - some of which include replacing the builder-grade flooring w/ Centurion Grey Polished Marble tiles t/o, California Closet systems installed in both walk-in closets, custom floor-to-ceiling metal & glass sliding doors w/ privacy glass, & built-in Murphy bed. Split floor plan design w/ open concept chef's kitchen - perfect for entertaining - features a 5-burner gas cooktop in the quartz waterfall island, professional Bosch appliances, inside full size laundry, Hunter Douglas electronic shades, premium Hodinke fans, & large view balcony - all meticulously maintained. Condo includes two (2) deeded parking spaces w/ dedicated EV Charging station & temperature controlled storage. Community offers wonderful amenities, including a large workout facility & adjacent stretching/pilates room, heated pool, Bocce ball, expansive rooftop terrace view deck (w/ massive gas fire pit, multiple BBQ grills, bar & sitting areas), dog washing station, and more! Minutes from everything - fine dining, shopping, parks, Sky Harbor Airport, Arts, entertainment and historic districts. HOA fee includes gas, water, sewer, trash, common area maintenance, & building security.

column9: Possibly the most highly upgraded home in Downtown Phx; This highly anticipated home is a rare work of art that only comes around once in a blue moon. Located in the heart of the Willo Historic District; this is the work of esteemed Designer Trent Hancock. This property boasts approximately 2, 600 total square feet with a two story casita that borders a raised designer pool, spa and sunken firepit area with a steel shade screen feature and a 1, 600 square foot main residence with all the bells and whistles you could dream of. This property is highly landscaped with an outdoor bbq, custom steel planters and mature desert plants and cactus. The main house interior has one of the most grand entry living rooms of any home downtown; featuring a vaulted Spanish style ebony wood ceiling and the original hardwood floors and an epic tiered Spanish fireplace. A dining room with a coffered wood ceiling and wet bar leads you to a new modern gourmet kitchen with Wolf/ Sub zero appliances and LED lit cabinets all with Sonos surround speakers leading to a lush backyard through floor to ceiling custom steel and glass doors. A luxe owners suite boasts a highly modernized bathroom that features a stand alone tub and walk in shower and also faces the pool and spa. Detached from the main house is a completely remodeled guest house/ casita. Downstairs features a vaulted exposed wood entry with cascading natural light pouring through skylights and feels like a Parisian artists Loft. This house won an ICONIC award for Historic Preservation and a Gold Nugget award from the Pacific Coast Builder Conference for best renovated home and was featured in Phoenix Home and Garden, a Waymo commercial, Zillow and Vrbo. When the owners travel they have had the home very successfully featured as an Airbnb. The owner spared no expense with this Historic; 100 year old Spanish Colonial residence that looks and feels more like a 5 star resort. Fully Modernized yet completely retaining its Historic charm; this home will leave you speechless.

column9: Now priced $58, 000 under the appraised value! ''House of Charm'' one of five built as a spec home by Paul Burroway. Relax on the gorgeous front porch or venture out into the backyard showcasing the refreshing pool and expansive lawn. The possibilities are endless with the detached storage/garage in the corner of the yard. Come see this one of a kind beauty and make it yours!

column9: This coveted ground-floor unit is the best that the luxury condo Tapestry on Central has to offer. column9: WELCOME TO WILLO! This fully restored and reimagined 100+ year old historic craftsman bungalow is unlike anything else in Willo. Known as the 'Walter Stone House' the wide front veranda greets you upon arrival and overlooks the beautiful landscaping and views of downtown. As you enter the home, you'll discover the hardwood floors and trim work have all been fully restored. Rumored to have once been occupied by Frank Lloyd Wright, a wall of mirrors added by the architect in the living room have been preserved and reflect the craftsman fireplace and corner built-ins. The kitchen offers custom cabinetry, premium appliances, gorgeous exposed brick and flows perfectly into the original breakfast nook and attached salon. The main house offers 3 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms - Both that have been remodeled with designer fixtures and finishes. The primary suite offers a large walk-in closet and opens out to a beautiful backyard with a large swimming pool and amazing outdoor living spaces that surround the home. A large detached structure offers an oversized garage and a full casita that's complete with its own bathroom, kitchen and sleeping loft. Every detail of this home has been thoughtfully planned and lovingly designed to respect the home's history while also maximizing its functionality and style. 108 W Almeria Road is ready to enjoy it's next 100 years - Welcome Home!

column9: UNICORN ALERT! This one is super special, it is nestled in the back of the only cul-de-sac in Willo and is so picturesque with a big tree in the circle, even a picnic table for an impromptu neighborhood block party! Inside this charmer features 3 large bedrooms plus a den/office and open floor plan. Boasting newer hardwood floors, updated appliances in the gorgeous kitchen, dual pane windows, newer AC unit, newer water heater & more, you can relax, this is a good one! The 2 car garage was renovated with AC/skylight and insulated door to make for a perfect artist studio or workshop. The yard...so amazing and lush with native trees and a 'sangria of fruit trees' you will love! There is even a huge shed and RV parking back there! This home ticks off the boxes that Willo loves, come see why!

column9: Charming 1920's bungalow with guest house in the heart of popular Willo Historic District! Main house 2br/1ba 1034', guest 1br/1ba 644'. Irresistible curb appeal with its grand overhanging eaves, diamond paned wood windows and cozy front porch. Gorgeous original pristine details inside including warm detailed woodwork, built-in cabinetry surrounding red brick fireplace, original wood floors and 9ft ceilings. Dining area with original built-in hutch. Updated kitchen w/ gas range new cabinetry. Lush backyard w/ gorgeous trees, gardens and wood deck patio. Very private detached guest house w/ separate yard area. Great setup with living room w/ sliding doors to yard, kitchen, bedroom/ full bath and laundry. Perfect for extra income or out of town guests! Must see!

column9: Experience urban luxury in this stunning 6th-floor unit featuring a split floor-plan with two ensuite bedrooms, a half bath, and no shared walls for unparalleled privacy. The coveted corner unit offers beautiful panoramic north/south views of the city skyline, mountains, and parks. Upgraded with high-end finishes, it includes SmartHome technology, electric shades, Caf Appliances, and Toto toilets with bidet features. Enjoy top-tier amenities such as a fully equipped gym, heated pool, rooftop lounge, firepits, BBQs, dog-wash and more. Located in the vibrant Roosevelt Row Arts District, you are steps from light rail, cultural hotspots, and restaurants, with three deeded parking spaces in the gated garage. Experience rare, quiet, urban living in the hottest zip code in Phoenix! THE DETAILS: Nestled between Portland Park, the Japanese Friendship Garden, Margaret T. Hance Park, and the RoRo, this south/north-facing unit provides outstanding vistas from every angle. The 20' balcony offers the perfect place for morning coffee, evening cocktails or peaceful supper while taking in the city skyline and mountain views. The monthly HOA is all inclusive, except for electricity. The plethora of services include: Internet, cable TV, natural gas, water, sewer, trash, gym, concierge/frond desk, security, building engineer, common area/amenities upkeep/maintenance, and blanket insurance. Luxury conveniences include SmartHome hub, Caf appliances, automated electric roller shades, programmable thermostats for the dual-zone HVAC units, 24 x24 porcelain terrazzo tile, plush carpeting in the ensuite bedrooms, Toto Toilets with Bio-Bidet remote control toilet seats, lighted/heated vanity mirrors, recessed LED lighting, ceiling fans, large walk-in closets, loads of storage, and tasteful decor throughout. In addition, the deed for this home includes a large on-site secured climate-controlled storage room, and 3 assigned parking spaces in the gated garage, one of which is on the same floor as the unit. Enjoy the convenience of a front desk concierge available six days a week and the peace of mind provided by nightly and weekend on-site security. The first floor is your gateway to relaxation and recreation, featuring a fully equipped gym, heated pool, bocce ball court, and BBQ grills with direct access to the park and Irish Cultural Center. The elegant lobby invites you to unwind by the two-sided gas fireplace, socialize in the indoor/outdoor gathering spaces, or find a quiet moment in the lounge area library. The rooftop beckons, where the ultimate chill space awaits. The sky lounge offers a gas firepit, large screen TV, BBQ grills, and an outdoor kitchen area, all framed by 360-degree views of the valley. For a more serene retreat, visit The Nest on the seventh floor, a quiet recessed exterior lounge area nestled above the treetops, overlooking the tranquil Japanese Friendship Garden. Additional conveniences include an on-site climate-controlled storage unit, dry-cleaning pick-up/delivery service, secure package pick-up/delivery, and grocery delivery handling, ensuring your daily needs are met effortlessly. The building enjoys street-front retail including Valley Coffee Company, Painters Lounge, Portland Dental, and Saint Pasta (coming soon, ) just steps away. Walk to dozens of restaurants and cultural experiences from Mid-down to Downtown. The Roosevelt Light Rail station is only a block away, offering easy access to the entire valley. Don't miss your chance to own a premium residence in the most sought-after high-rise in the valley. This is more than just a home, it's a lifestyle. Don't wait!

column9: WELCOME TO WILLO! This classic cottage was built in 1936 and offers unique architecture that was less common for this time period. From the large covered front porch, you'll enjoy lush landscaping and beautiful views of the Midtown skyline. As you enter, you'll discover the house maintains its historic charm with original wood floors, a gorgeous fireplace, beautiful vintage tile, and the classic details that make historic homes so special. As you step outside to the backyard, you'll find a huge covered patio overlooking the gardens that's perfect for outdoor living and a detached oversized one car garage that has so many possibilities. Walking distance to everything in Midtown, this location feels like a small town in the city!

Don't miss out on the perfect downtown living experience!! Rare find with 2 parking spaces in garage!!

column9: This duplex has 2 units, both units have 5 bedrooms and 2.5 baths each. Both are rented with guaranteed $3, 028.08 per unit (including tax) a month from the city of Phoenix with 1 year leases in place. Each unit has the primary bedroom downstairs along with the kitchen, family room and 1/2 bath. There are 4 bedrooms and a bathroom upstairs along with a walkout balcony that over looks downtown Phoenix. These are all new construction and come with a 1 year full builder warranty. Both units have a large 2 car carport and small private backyard as well, each unit is separately meter for water and electric both.

column9: Make your move to this charming 3 bed, 2 bath Tudor Revival in the heart of Willo Historic District! A tasteful blend of modern comfort with historic personality featuring oak wood floors, archways, high ceilings, gable roof and gated porte-cochre. A desirable and functional floor plan welcomes you to a large living room with fireplace, dining room with French doors leading to the front porch, plus updated kitchen with quaint breakfast nook. Great, natural light throughout. Enjoy a spacious, private backyard with patio and dining, grassy play area, mature landscaping, and detached garage. Home improvements include roof, windows and HVAC (see full list in docs tab). This gem sits on one of the most charming streets in Willo and near all that Midtown & Downtown Phoenix has to offer

column9: WELCOME TO WILLO! This Mid-Century home has been reimagined to embrace the modern style that was intended. Great curb appeal with unique design features greet you upon arrival. Inside you'll find that all of the classic MCM features have been preserved and enhanced with modern design details. A large living room and family room connect perfectly into the dining area and kitchen to create an excellent floor plan. The kitchen features stone counters, custom wood elements, and designer finishes. Three bedrooms all open to the backyard offering amazing indoor/outdoor living with this resort style backyard. A built-in BBQ, custom planters and incredible patio spaces all surround a beautiful private pool. A drive through garage and detached office provide additional amenities. Located in this AMAZING neighborhood within walking distance to your favorite restaurants and everything in the Art's District - This property is one of a kind. WELCOME HOME!

column9: This is the one with the views! A truly luxurious Penthouse at Tapestry On Central. South facing with downtown Phoenix skyline and mountain views. Enjoy sunsets and city views from the large roof top patios and decks. This home is spacious and well maintained. Beautiful engineered hardwood in all the right places and large builder upgraded tile. Upgraded granite in the kitchen and baths with undermount sinks. Don't forget about the convenience of the light rail stop just steps away. Just a few stops to restaurants, museums, arts and the downtown sports complex. Do you travel? You can take the like rail right to Phoenix Sky Harbor and save on parking! There is so much within walking distance too. Check out the Oven & Vine for happy hour and there is even a nail salon at Tapestry. Tapestry has secured underground parking and this unit comes with two parking spaces. You don't want to miss this opportunity for Midtown Phoenix living!

column9: Discover the Welch House, a 1928 original Craftsman bungalow listed on the National Register of Historic Places. This Roosevelt Historic District gem blends the timeless quality and design of the era, even including the root cellar with the additional function of ample parking and storage of its acclimated 2 car detached drive-thru garage and bonus office/suite & bath.Great possibility for an ADU with bathroom, sewer and water already in place! Step back in time with original wood flooring, bannisters, trim & lead glass sash windows. Cozy up by the living room's fireplace with its original log kit, and entertain in the classic Craftsman dining room. The bright and airy kitchen allows space for an island work area, and even boasts a vintage 1950 O'Keefe and Merritt gas stove! MORE... ...Enjoy peace of mind with a new roof (2023), AC(2016)& garage cooler(2016). plus updated plumbing and electrical systems. A spacious office with a closet and full bath provides a serene workspace downstairs while the upstairs three large bedrooms await, including a master suite with a 10x10 walk-in closet. The detached two-car garage includes a finished room with a half bath and roughed-in shower. Relax on the wrap-around porch with original details, surrounded by lush green yards. Just a block from Hance Park and moments from downtown Phoenix's vibrant scene, this is more than a home - it's a piece of history waiting for you...HVAC 2016 GARAGE COOLER 2023

column9: This is a must see Midtown Phoenix condo located at Tapestry On Central. Enjoy urban living in one of the best 2 bedroom floor plans in the city. It's move in ready and even has new energy efficient Anderson windows. Other features are beautiful engineered hardwood in living and bedroom areas and upgraded tile in the kitchen and baths. The kitchen features granite, newer stainless appliances and new stainless sink and faucet. The ensuite has upgraded granite and undermount sinks. You will enjoy some of the best views offered in the city too. The Phoenix light rail stop is just steps away from your door at the Central/Encanto station. You can take the light rail to the many local restaurants downtown or uptown, visit the arts district and sports complex down You can also take it right to Sky Harbor and not have to worry about parking. Tapestry has amenities on site such as fitness center, heated pool & spa & secure underground parking. There is even a Walgreens Pharmacy, Nail Salon and more on site too. Don't miss out this home will go fast!

column9: Tapestry On Central is Phoenix Urban Living at its finest. This upgraded Tapestry condo is move in ready and one bedroom units at Tapestry don't come available often. It's truly one of the best one bedroom floor plans around. The layout make it feel much larger than most one bedrooms. The interior features beautiful upgraded wood flooring in living and bedroom areas and tile in the kitchen and bath. There's newer paint and accent walls throughout. The kitchen has beautiful granite, white cabinets, stainless appliances and new stainless sink and faucet. This home even has a large bathroom with separate soaker tub and shower. Enjoy the west city views and sunsets off your north facing balcony. When it's too hot outside enjoy the comfort of your condo with the newer AC unit. This unit comes complete with in unit LG front loading washer and dryer. Tapestry has amenities on site such as fitness center, heated pool & spa & secure underground parking. There is even a Walgreens Pharmacy, Nail Salon and more on site too. The Phoenix light rail stop is just steps away from your door at the Central/Encanto station. You can take the light rail to the many local restaurants downtown or uptown, visit the arts district and sports complex downtown. You can also take it right to Sky Harbor and not have to worry about parking. This home will go fast!

column9: 801 S 1st Ave is a triplex situated on a corner lot in Downtown Phoenix. The mix consists of (2) 1bed/1bath and (1) 3bed/1bath units, all separate buildings that are individually metered for electricity and fenced with private yards. Plenty of parking and residents have quick access to attractions like Footprint Center, Chase Field, Roosevelt Row and all of the vibrant restaurants, bars and entertainment spaces Downtown Phoenix has to offer. This triplex presents a great opportunity for investors looking for a value add opportunity or a short erm rental. Units were recently renovated/modernized by the seller (roof/kitchens/bedrooms/exterior/etc) but a new owner can expand on these to further optimize rents. Drive by only. Do not disturb tenants.

column9: Priced below comps & ready for new owners! Updated & remodeled with permits, this Willo home will make you smile from the moment you see it--until the moment you leave. IF you ever leave! Featuring 4 bedrooms, 2 baths & an amazing kitchen with top-of-the-line appliances, a large island-and ability to convert garage to guest house. Primary bedroom features a WALK IN closet, gorgeous bath & private entrance to a large back yard. There is also a super functional mudroom with laundry, tankless water heater & multiple patios ideal for hanging with friends & family. A rare find in & of itself & it has a 2 car detached garage (that would be an easy guest house conversion!), plus parking for 6 more cars, too! The yard is generously sized, and yes, that is a detached shed with electrical Kitchen features amazing appliances, gorgeous copper hood, and a bold green color palette on the cabinets. Green not your thing? The custom cabinets are painted with a specialty paint that allows them to be easily resurfaced/repainted (read: Super cost effective! See photos for example of an all-white color palette).

column9: WELCOME TO WILLO! Classic Spanish style curb appeal with a fully gated front yard greet you upon arrival. Fantastic open concept floor plan with chef's kitchen & designer finishes. Separate family room & huge laundry room/pantry provide incredible storage. Gorgeous natural light flows throughout the house with a massive primary suite at the rear of the home. Multiple French doors open out to the beautiful outdoor living areas with this HUGE 10, 000+ sq ft lot providing a stunning pool, spa, sport court & a 3 CAR GARAGE! Welcome Home!

column9: UNICORN ALERT!! Tucked in the middle of one of the coolest historic districts, this elegant cottage charm in WILLO is truly a special find! Step back in time and enjoy barrel vaulted ceilings, arched doorways, and exterior stonework surrounded by modern day beauty. Bamboo and travertine floors, quartz countertops, and designer lighting, as well as lots of natural light, add to the charm! French doors in every bedroom will lead you to your private oasis. The garage gives you ample space to store all of your treasures. A beautifully crafted tile mosaic and mural on the wall add beauty in every direction! You won't want to miss this one!

column9: artHAUS townhouse for sale! The larger, coveted, 2 bed, 3 bath, end unit with only one neighbor is a rare find! Large living room with giant windows that let in amazing natural light and city views. The kitchen includes huge kitchen island, beautiful custom cabinets, stainless steel appliances and sliding glass doors that lead out to the common area. This home has 3 interior levels with white interior walls and a wood plank staircase that leads to a large master bedroom attached to a 3/4 bathroom with double sinks, a glass door shower, and a roomy custom walk-in closet. Upstairs laundry with washer and dryer is super convenient. Sliding doors lead to a balcony overlooking a beautiful view of the historic Willow Neighborhood. Gated parking. Additional amenities include master bedroom split, separate exterior storage, covered parking and more. Enjoy living with in walking distance to great restaurants and just a bike ride away from downtown! HOA Includes Water, Sewer & Garbage

column9: WELOME TO WILLO! This incredible Tudor is what living in the Willo Historic District is all about. Classic curb appeal with a beautiful covered entry greet you upon arrival. Inside you will discover INCREDIBLE vaulted ceilings, dark stained wood beams & exposed brick. The living room is truly striking as you look upstairs to the loft and see the stained glass window in the peak. Coved ceilings, hardwood floors & other original features have been preserved throughout. The dining room is grand in size and opens to the kitchen which has fantastic storage and even includes a separate breakfast nook. The rest of the main level offers two bedrooms, a beautifully remodeled bathroom and a den that opens to the staircase. Upstairs you will find the primary suite and a loft that opens to below. Outside the property offers great outdoor living with a large yard and a detached garage. Perfectly located within the neighborhood and walking distance to all of your Midtown favorites. WELCOME HOME!

column9: RARE find in Downtown Phoenix!! This beautifully preserved yet updated and spacious condo is a must- see.The historic building was meticulously updated from original in 2001. Updates from the developer include covered + garage parking for all owners. More recently in 2023; newly remodeled bathrooms, primary and secondary built in closet systems, and open floorpan perfectly blend cozy, modern aspects with a historic, industrial style. Just steps away from ASU Downtown Campus, Roosevelt Row, Diamondbacks & Suns facilities, and more, this condo is the complete picture of downtown PHX living.

column9: Great opportunity to own a property in the highly sought after Portland Place Condo Community! Situated in a prime Downtown Phoenix location providing unparalleled convenience & access to the city's vibrant offerings. Discover a testament to modern living w/a spacious floor plan highlighted by soaring ceilings, floor-to-ceiling windows, & beautiful tile floors throughout. The kitchen is a cook's delight, featuring SS appliances, gas cooktop & a wall oven. Granite tile counters, wood shaker cabinetry, stylish tile backsplash, recessed lighting, a walk-in pantry, & a breakfast bar elevate the space. Primary retreat is a haven of comfort with a full bathroom, a walk-in closet, & patio access. The sizable back patio w/pavers underfoot promises serene mornings. Unit is steps away from garage Room darkening window treatments stay with the home. Inside laundry area off of kitchen along with half bath.

column9: Charming and well maintained home in Historic Willow District of Phoenix. Great curb appeal with brick walkway leading to home. Classic touches throughout.Spacious Living room with brick fireplace and picture window. Kitchen boast kitchen nook with brick wall and white cabinets. Master with private exit and room for sitting area. Spacious covered patio and free standing garage with capability to be a guest suite/office. Great condition and value in Willo. Roof replaced appx 8 years ago, HVAC replaced 6 years ago sewer lines and gas lines replaced recently. Walk to locally owned restaurants, museums, downtown, Encanto park (and golf!) Near St. Joseph's Hospital and popular downtown sporting events and concerts. Receiving property tax break for owner occupants

column9: Craftsman bungalow in historic Roosevelt, close to everything DTPHX! Original HDWD floors, built ins, fireplace and covered porch. $250K addition designed to the original character: new chef's kitchen, primary bedroom/bath, laundry room! Significant tax advantage-Historic Neighborhood Designation. Owned solar system, 3 climate zone HVAC, and brand new appliances-extremely efficient. Utilities buried - ready for custom pool, blue prints included. Large carport, 3 driveway spots, car outlet, and RV gate. Mature landscaping: trees, low maint. desert front yard, turf back, and new irrigation. Casita with side entrance for office, guest room, or rental. Insulated attic and shed for extra storage. The kitchen features all new Frigidaire 66 Professional Series side by side column refrigerator and freezer, ILVE 6 burner Italian dual convection oven w rotisserie, griddle, and pot filler (gas burners, electric oven) ZLine professional range hood. American Walnut butcher block counter tops, with a Brazilian Quartzite center island(large 33 x22 single bowl stainless steel sink in island). Built in 2 door dual temp wine/beverage fridge. The laundry room addition features new Electrolux washer and dryer. Tankless hot water heaters in the main home and casita. Water softener to help protect the new appliances. The recent addition also includes a large primary bedroom and en suite with dual sinks, walk-in closet, and impressive shower. Experience modern living with vintage charm, as you relax on your front porch swing to the palm tree lined street views of this charming historical neighborhood.

column9: So many options with this incredible property! Currently an office, the existing zoning allows residential, office or even coffee shops and retail! Built circa 1913 and professionally restored in 2005, the quality of this brick bungalow is nearly unheard of in Phoenix! Main house is 1574 sq ft with 3 beds and 2 baths plus den and studio in back is an additional 324 sq ft with wetbar, perfect for home office or art studio. Live/work opportunity! Special features include real wood floors, custom tile in both baths, claw foot tub, oiled soapstone countertops, 5 panel doors, oiled bronze hardware, original woodwork, stone fireplace, beautiful light fixtures. Also has underground utilities, automatic gate, private lush yard, good parking and a 1961 BOMB SHELTER! Incredible unique property!

Custom built cabinets in the family room, freshly painted exterior RV gate and parking. No HOA. Large Garage in the rear of the home. Historical district property tax breaks and incentives.

column9: Nestled in heart of downtown, The Diamond House, a 1912 Craftsman Bungalow, is a living testament to history, proudly chronicled in the National Registry of Historic Places. This architectural masterpiece has been lovingly restored, sparing no detail, preserving its original character while seamlessly blending in modern conveniences. This large lot and home boast 4 generously large bedrooms, 2 baths, an office, & a sitting room outside the upstairs primary, each room filled with character and charm. The remodeled upstairs bathroom & closet are a MUST see! The backyard is an ABSOLUTE entertainers dream! With the new grandiose pergola covering the outdoor patio, heated diving pool featuring an elongated Baja shelf and spa, with plenty of outdoor space for lounging and games. The central fireplace serves as a warm focal point, complemented by lofty 10-foot ceilings. The stunning stained and etched glass detail within the house add a touch of elegance and craftsmanship that's rarely seen today. Seller added a split unit AC to the wrap around solarium, bringing in the natural light and comfort in all seasons. Additional highlights include a basement for extra storage space and a balcony that offers a quiet retreat. But that's not all - this home also features a newly rebuilt garage, complete with the restoration of its original ceiling and the addition of a new AC system. The property has been thoughtfully enhanced with buried electrical lines, limestone pavers, a newly poured concrete driveway, and a sewer line replacement and relocation at the rear. The culmination of these elements makes The Diamond House a true masterpiece of historic preservation and modern luxury, making it a must-see for those who appreciate the rich tapestry of architectural history.

column9: WELCOME TO WILLO! This red brick bungalow has been beautifully enhanced & preserved. As you enter, you'll find original wood floors, archways, built-ins and incredible coved ceiling details throughout. The bathroom has been perfectly remodeled with a period style, complimented by designer tile & finishes. The kitchen features custom cabinetry with great storage. Amazing upgrades throughout that are so hard to find in a historic home with incredible natural light that flows throughout this home perfectly. Outside the backyard is made for outdoor living with a massive patio & lush landscaping! This one of a kind home is truly rare. WELCOME HOME

Upstairs laundry. Highly desirable downtown location.

column9: This pristine property has been placed on THE NATIONAL REGISTER OF HISTORIC PLACES BY THE US DEPARTMENT OF THE INTERIOR AND BUILT IN 1927. Included in the property is a renovated 480 Sq. Ft. Casita in the back yard with vaulted ceilings and hardwood flooring--perfect for a home office or guest, making it a 3 BED/3 BATH. This home has the perfect blend of modern updates, character, and charm. Newly remodeled kitchen with SS appliances and Quartz countertops. Hardwood flooring throughout. Large front porch covered in Satillo tile. Backyard has a covered patio with a large pool that has been newly resurfaced - surrounded by lush landscaping. Willo is in close proximity to Downtown Phoenix attractions and the Roosevelt Arts District. Come visit this gem of a property!

Walk out the kitchen french doors and be greeted by an amazing pool, spa, perfect landscaping, large covered patio with infrared heating, 2 car garage, casita, heck there is even a playhouse! 10++

column9: UNICORN ALERT! Welcome to the 1927 Lamar Building, a historic gem of 1920's Phoenix. This two-story wire-cut brick structure underwent meticulous relocation and restoration in 2004 to become the charming townhome it is today. You are greeted at the front stoop with views of the gleaming hardwood floors, high ceilings, fantastic walls of windows allowing for lots of natural light to show this place off. Updated kitchen with custom cabinets and all views look over the fabulous back yard with a pool/spa/firepit/BBQ area..it really is the perfect yard for all seasons! Upstairs are the bedrooms, the primary is huge with treetop views and 2 walk in closets. The 2nd bedroom had a bonus area, perfect for an office w/ amazing downtown skyline views. Walk to Hance Park, Japanese Garden & more!

column9: Immerse yourself in the allure of Modern Farmhouse Elegance with a NEW ROOF; this harvest haven awaits you! This charming residence, featuring 3 bedrooms and 3 bathrooms, exudes character and showcases curb appeal that encapsulates the essence of Willo's timeless charm. Upon entering, experience a seamless fusion of classic allure and modern farmhouse style. The generously sized bedrooms offer ample space for rest and relaxation, each with its own unique charm. The three bathrooms boast elegant fixtures and thoughtful design, transforming every morning routine into a delightful experience. Bask in the Arizona sunshine in your private pool oasis within the solitude of your backyard, creating the perfect setting for relaxation, entertainment, and lasting memories with family and friends. Designed with daily comfort in mind, the air-conditioned garage ensures a comfortable space for your vehicles, coupled with ample storage for your convenience. Nestled in the heart of the Willo Historic District, this home is surrounded by a captivating blend of historic architecture and vibrant urban living. Enjoy the proximity to downtown Phoenix, where a myriad of cultural events, dining, shopping, and entertainment options await. This home is the epitome of a perfect blend of historical allure and modern amenities. Don't miss the rare opportunity to own a piece of history with all the conveniences one could wish for. Whether you seek to entertain or create a tranquil retreat, this Willo gem fulfills every desire. Step into a world of timeless elegance and comfort!

column9: Here's your chance to own the Harry J. Rolls house in the Willo Historic District! This charming brick, period revival home is located on the coveted Palm Lane. The fantastic curb appeal and front porch welcomes you right away. Spacious interiors include a beautiful living room with fireplace, formal dining room, remodeled kitchen with breakfast nook, remodeled bathroom, architectural niches and historic charm throughout. Large pantry and laundry room. Brand new beautiful roof, updated electrical and HVAC. Attached garage - rare for historic - wonderful backyard with lots of grass and out building that could be used as an office/gym/studio. Walk to all the wonderful amenities of Midtown including Phoenix Art Museum, Heard Museum, great restaurants, bars and light rail.

column9: Wow! Midtown Luxury under $400k and only $265/sqft! This gently lived in Midtown Phoenix condo is super clean, freshly painted and move in ready! It's like living in the historic Willo district yet having the convenience of urban living being just steps from the light rail stop. Features include upgraded appliances, granite, gas range and a gas fireplace. The first floor has nice large tile throughout. The large upstairs bedrooms each have its own private bath and plenty of closet space. Just minutes from shopping via a short drive or the light rail. This home has two assigned parking spaces in the secure underground parking too. Great for unloading groceries! On site amenities include a fitness center, club house, large heated pool and spa, a Walgreen pharmacy is on site, nail salon, and a new art studio too.

column9: A 1940 pre-war home located in the Willo district with the cutest Dutch door offers 3 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, new exterior/interior paint, indoor laundry, and a casita that's not included in your bedroom/bathroom count. The primary suite was beautifully renovated and offers an en-suite with double sinks, free standing soaking tub, walk in shower, and designer Hinkley lighting with an additional flex space for yoga, meditation, study and more. Your opportunity is endless with an existing casita needing TLC, a blank canvas for your landscape dreams, and the coveted location of Willo. This charming neighborhood offers community, walkability to Pino's Pizza, Songbird, Oven + Vine, Durant's, and so much more. Close proximity to St. Joe's Hospital, I-10, the light rail, grocery stores

column9: Charming Tudor home built in 1931 and located on an idyllic street in the coveted Willo Historic District. Preserved coved ceilings, original hardwood floors and unique archways throughout historic living areas of home. Chef's kitchen featuring walnut counters, hand-painted backsplash tile, 36'' KitchenAid gas range with stainless hood vent, open shelving and custom cabinets. The kitchen flows seamlessly into the family room and spacious primary bedroom addition. Stacking washer/dryer & basement for storage. Backyard offers a tree shaded paver patio, irrigated planting beds and custom iron gates. New permitted casita or office offers tremendous versatility. As one of the first historic districts, Willo is steps away from the light rail, incredible dining, culture and amenities Phx offer.

column9: WELCOME TO WILLO! This Historic Art Modern Home has been beautifully restored and reimagined. This architecture style was very RARE in the 1930's and the home offers striking curb appeal! Inside you'll find original etched concrete floors, tall cove ceilings, corner windows, and exquisite archways. The black dining room compliments the home's modern roots and creates a dramatic contrast within the home. The kitchen maintains its original features but has been beautifully elevated with CUSTOM cabinets, paneled appliances and a fantastic 36'' gas range. The bathrooms offer period tile that has been enhanced with designer wallpaper and new fixtures and finishes throughout. Great floor plan with large bedrooms and direct access outside to the HUGE backyard. Enjoy lush green grass with great patio spaces for outdoor living and skyline views! Beyond the yard, you'll find a large two car garage complete with plumbing, sewer, and electric that creates so many opportunities. This unique home is perfectly located with easy access to all of your Midtown favorites. WELCOME HOME!

column9: Charming 1941 Transitional Ranch home in the heart of the Willo Historic District. The property consists of 3 bedrooms, 2 en-suite, and 3 baths. (The 3rd bedroom is currently used as an office.) The formal living room features a gas fireplace. The living and dining rooms have beautiful French doors which provide great light and open to front and rear patios. The eat-in kitchen has been beautifully remodeled with an island and a Wolf gas range. The primary suite also has French doors to a rear patio, a walk-in closet and a full bath with separate tub and shower. The backyard features a covered patio, a heated, pebble-tech pool, a natural gas built-in BBQ & firepit & a detached guest suite/office with a bathroom, as well as a 2 car garage, storage room and an air conditioned laundry room.

column9: Extremely rare Historic property in the Blount Addition. This property is nearly original and has not been offered for sale in decades. The attributes and character you have been looking for are right here! Brick fireplace, original cabinets, light fixtures and hardwood flooring. Documented envelope and duct tape sealing with extra insulation! Jazz stucco never needs repainting. Huge private lot exceeding 9500sf, makes this property truly one of a kind-and it comes complete with detached two car garage! Live literally steps from Hance Park anda a quick walk to light rail and Roosevelt Row. Don't forget the tax advantages of living in a historic property. Let the spirit of 1920's Phoenix enrobe you. A chance of a lifetime to make your dream come true!

column9: Beautiful 2, 360 SF, 3 Bedroom and 3 Bathroom Primary Home PLUS a Detached One Bedroom and One Bathroom Guest Casita located in the coveted Willo Historic District, in the heart of Downtown Phoenix! This solid brick construction home is oozing with the charm and character of the 1940's but has also been extensively renovated in recent years with updated cosmetic features including a gourmet kitchen, gorgeous custom-tile bathrooms, stained and polished concrete flooring, and hand-picked fixtures and finishes that complement the mid-century modern architecture and style. Major recent improvements include Full Roof Replacement on both main house and casita (2019), New 5 Ton Split HVAC for main house (2019), New Mini-Split for casita including all new electrical and panel upgrades (2019), New Landscaping in Backyard and Carport Area including Travertine Tiles, Artificial Turf, and Relocation of HVAC unit to a newly fenced side yard (2020), New Interior and Exterior Paint for both the main home and casita (2022 and 2020 respectively), New Tankless Water Heater for casita (2021), New stained tongue and groove pine boards, recessed lighting, and smart outlets/switches for the casita patio ceiling (2023), New Sewer Lines Complete to City Hook-Ups (2018), Updated Electrical Wiring (2018), and so much more! Please see Documents Tab for a complete list of recent improvements! The large Primary Bedroom Suite includes a dual-head, custom-tiled shower, free standing soaking tub, and an extended-height quartz vanity with 2 sink basins. Secondary Bedroom Suite includes an ensuite bathroom with custom-tiled shower, quartz counter vanity, and a private entry to the backyard / patio. The third bedroom in the main home, currently being used as an office, is located next to a full guest bathroom with a custom-tiled shower/tub combo with quartz counter vanity. The well-laid out kitchen includes quartz counter tops, white shaker cabinets with 42 uppers, expansive wall-pantry with ample storage, and stainless steel appliances including a built-in wine fridge and gas range. Entertain guests in the large open living room and separate dining room that serves as the hub of the home. Head out back to find the updated casita that is perfect for a home office, guest quarters, or an income producing property as a short-term rental. Grill out and enjoy the beautiful Arizona weather in your custom-landscaped backyard or if you don't feel like cooking, walk to one of the many, top-rated local restaurants. Make a full night of it and take the light-rail down to cheer on the Suns or D-Backs, catch a show, explore one of the new art galleries Downtown. The Willo neighborhood is in close proximity to St. Joseph's Hospital, Barrow Neurological Institute, Phoenix Children's Hospital, Banner University Medical Center, ASU Downtown Campus, U of A Medical School, and numerous employers in Midtown and Downtown Phoenix.

column9: Urban living at its best! This remodeled Tapestry On Central condo is move in ready. Located In the heart of Midtown Phoenix it has the perfect modern urban feel. The interior features beautiful upgraded flooring, custom paint and accent walls. Solid wood cabinets, custom tile feature, quartz counters and upgraded appliances in the chef's kitchen. The laundry room off the kitchen has an upgraded washer & dryer too. There is modern shutters on all windows and your guest room/office is complete with a remodeled private bath. Sit on your large patio or balcony year around with a north facing view of the open courtyard. Tapestry has amenities on site such as fitness center & heated pool & spa. There is a Walgreens Pharmacy, Nail Salon and more on site too. A light rail stop is just steps away from your door. You can take the light rail to the many local restaurants, the arts district and sports complex. You can also take it right to Sky Harbor and not have to worry about parking. Don't miss this one! Remodeled units of this floorplan do not come up often.

column9: UNICORN ALERT! Oh yes, this one really is a unicorn! RARELY do you see this floor plan come available, and even more rare to be a NW corner unit with spectacular views like this! Awesome sunsets, Camelback Mountain, Uptown City Views and of course, the Japanese Friendship Garden and Hance Park is right there! Perched on the 11th floor, this one bedroom unit has floor to ceiling glass with dual slider doors leading out to arguably the best seat in the house from the wrap around balcony! Large Island kitchen with a big window over the sink (Realtors swooned at this!) and an eat in kitchen table make the best use of space. Large bath with a huge walk in shower, plus an oversized walk in closet. Community rooftop, pool, gym, common areas are the hallmark of Portland on the Park. A true 10++!
