column9: Midtown luxury condo! Nicely updated and upgraded. This 5th floor home is North facing and has fantastic views of the uptown Phoenix skyline and mountains. All on one level with split bedrooms plus a 3rd room perfect for a nursery, bedroom or den. There are even gorgeous built-ins from California closets in the den, laundry and walk-in closet! It's move-in-ready with newer LVT flooring and baseboards throughout, new kitchen this year with pull out cabinets, soft closed drawers and doors and new appliances. There are 2 assigned parking spots in the gated underground parking. You will be steps away from the light rail that can transport you some of Phoenix's best attractions including theaters, sports arena, ball park and concert halls. There is a Walgreen's Pharmacy and Nail Salon on site too.

column9: Rare opportunity to own a complete restoration of a 1920s Tudor in the heart of popular Willo Historic District! This red brick Tudor w/ turret and shake roof has amazing curb appeal w/ lush trees and large patio at front entrance. Home was completely gutted/ renovated between 2011-2015. Living room with barreled/ beamed ceilings w/ gas fireplace and French doors to side yard. Brazilian hardwood floors t/o. Gourmet kitchen opens to dining room and extraordinary built-in breakfast room banquet in the Turret. Viking gas range w/ custom metal hood, Wolf microwave & wall oven, Subzero fridge/ freezer, walk-in pantry, repurposed brick wall. Gorgeous master suite w/ separate entrance to back. New 700sq' basement w/ 10' ceilings, large family room and full bath. Detached 2CG w/ AC & 2 exits. See floorplan and complete features list in Documents tab.

column9: This impeccably maintained 1937 Cape Cod historic home is situated in the highly sought-after Willo District. With 2 bedrooms and 1.5 baths, this generously sized dwelling encompasses 1, 721 square feet, resting on an expansive lot of almost 7, 500 square feet. The separate garage/workshop offers ample room for both parking and storage needs. Sellers have approved plans and permits to convert into a casita! Huge Value-Add Potential! Abundant natural light fills the interior, highlighting the lovingly preserved original details and added upgrades like original floors, hardware fixtures and wainscoting. Property has misting system and electric charger. This historic home places you within close proximity to downtown amenities, encompassing shopping, dining, and entertainment!

column9: WELCOME TO WILLO! AS-IS SALE! This Classic Tudor Revival offers striking curb appeal with an amazing front porch to enjoy the neighborhood. WELCOME HOME!

column9: WELCOME TO WILLO. A large pillared veranda with beautiful curb appeal welcomes you to this Classic Willo home offering southern charm in the city. As you enter, you'll discover a grand living room and dining room with an original fireplace, soaring ceilings and gorgeous custom trim work. The kitchen features an Italian Range, original terrazzo counters and designer details that elevate the vintage design. Down the striking corridor you'll find two bedroom suites, each with fantastic closets and beautiful terrazzo bathrooms that have been enhanced to offer historic elegance. This wonderful floor plan opens to a private backyard where you will enjoy a large covered patio, great outdoor living, and a detached office. Walking distance to everything in midtown - WELCOME HOME!

column9: Back On Market!! This updated gem in the Willo Historic District is an incredibly charming 1937 Bungalow home featuring a great floor plan, 350 sf finished attic consisting of 1BR & 1/2 bath, balcony w/ mid-town views, enclosed sun room & 400 sf finished basement. Other great features include 9' & 10' high ceilings throughout, spacious living area, over-sized bedrooms, new & refinished flooring, remodeled bathroom, open kitchen & large yard. Additional climate-controlled & insulated casita-like space w/ 1/2 bath can be used for office, additional living space or home gym. Phenomenal Historic District location, close to vibrant local amenities & cultural attractions of downtown PHX w/in walking distance of light rail, restaurants & the best neighborhood feel in metro PHX. Welcome Home!

column9: This could be an amazing historic restoration project. On the National Register of Historic Properties, the City of Phoenix Historic Preservation Office would love to see it designated and there may be funding for it's restoration available. The ''Market'' is open space and the secondary building had four units originally, but could be renovated into fewer units. There are also two other units to the south of Market building that have been burned out, but may still be able to be restored and renovated. See documents tab for information from the Historic Preservation Office at the City of Phoenix. Call listing agent for more information.

column9: WELCOME TO WILLO! Step inside this MID-CENTURY Ranch that has been beautifully modernized to enhance its original design. Built by famous architect Charles Schreiber in 1950 as his personal residence, you'll find exposed wood beam ceilings, an original flagstone fireplace, incredible windows and designer details throughout! Four bedrooms, three bathrooms, a private office, huge laundry room, great storage & a floor plan that was made to entertain with fantastic living spaces that open to the resort style backyard. As you step outside, you'll be amazed by the outdoor living with the heated pool & spa. Homes this size are a rare find in Willo & it's located in the heart of this special Historic District within walking distance to everything that Midtown has to offer. WELCOME HOME!

column9: Stop n smell the roses...this amazing remodel needs to be experienced, 1 step at a time-drink in the finishes of a historic Willo smart home with the view of the backyard oasis. Owned by a single family prior to the remodel, this design keeps the original historic feel, while allowing you contemporary function-even voice/app control of features. Has smooth texture, handmade Zellige tile, exposed gorgeous brick wall, new roof/AC/windows/plumbing/electrical. Kitchen has quartz countertops & chic green cabinets. Cook using the herbs/vegetables of the raised garden bed outside. 2370 SF includes 196SF basement & 432 SF casita/mother-in-law suite/Airbnb! 2 car detached garage. Enjoy the different perspectives as you explore the yard & 4 entertaining spaces-dining terrace/fire pit areas.Grab it! Main house has 2 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms and the casita has a kitchenette/living room and a bedroom and bathroom.

column9: UNICORN ALERT! Oh yes, this one really is a unicorn! RARELY do you see this floor plan come available, and even more rare to be a NW corner unit with spectacular views like this! Awesome sunsets, Camelback Mountain, Uptown City Views and of course, the Japanese Friendship Garden and Hance Park is right there! Perched on the 11th floor, this one bedroom unit has floor to ceiling glass with dual slider doors leading out to arguably the best seat in the house from the wrap around balcony! Large Island kitchen with a big window over the sink (Realtors swooned at this!) and an eat in kitchen table make the best use of space. Large bath with a huge walk in shower, plus an oversized walk in closet. Community rooftop, pool, gym, common areas are the hallmark of Portland on the Park. A true 10++!

column9: NYC in Phoenix! Live like you're in Manhattan, just without the rain and snow. 407 at Orpheum Lofts is located in one of the few walkable parts of town, with a Valley Metro Rail station just a block away at Jefferson & 1st Ave. Roosevelt Row, Footprint Center, and more all within walking distance. Exposed brick walls, vaulted concrete ceilings, exposed pipes, and a wall of windows complete the NYC loft aesthetic. Orpheum Lofts is one of the few pre-war condominiums in AZ. Built in 1931 as the Title and Trust building, it was later converted to condominiums in 2005. Amenities include a part-time doorman, package room, billiards room, conference room, pool, fitness center, private storage, and more. Homes at Orpheum are eligible for a historic property tax credit, if owner occupie

column9: WELCOME TO WILLO! This special home offers incredible curb appeal with a large front patio that showcases beautiful city views! Inside you'll enjoy hardwood floors, original trim work, built-ins and gorgeous tall cove ceilings. The kitchen and bathroom have both been modernized to offer new fixtures and designer finishes. Two large bedrooms offer great storage and you'll love the HUGE primary closet with laundry! Fantastic basement offering a private office and family room! Outside you'll find what outdoor living is all about with a wonderful covered patio that overlooks the lush backyard, gardens, and garage. Enjoy the best of city living within a neighborhood that feels like a small town and is in walking distance to everything that Midtown offers! WELCOME HOME!

Excellent opportunity for fix and flip.

column9: As you step into this beautiful retreat, you feel instantly calm. The soft hues, refined wood plank floors, two-sided fireplace, lofty ceilings, and spa-like primary ensuite make you feel perfectly at home. $80, 000 professional renovation in 2022, and the finishes are contemporary and refined-a perfect touch in this fabulous open corner unit. Overlooking the Japanese Friendship Garden with splendid views south and west, there are two patios for bennys with mimosas or that perfect happy hour cocktail. A basket of culinary delights and bubbly are the perfect addition for a roof terrace dinner and a lovely swim, with 360 views forever. Don't miss this special home.

column9: Beautifully updated craftsman bungalow located in Phoenix! With hardwood floors and an updated kitchen, this unique 3 bed 2 bath home has tons to offer. Huge bay window in the dining room. Brick fireplace in living room. Custom design in both bathrooms. The master suite provides private access to the backyard, built-ins in the bathroom, and two walk-in closets. Don't forget the basement which would be great for additional storage! Outside you'll find a large elevated patio and a hot tub! Solar Panel loan to be paid in full by owner through escrow.

column9: This is the one! A truly luxurious Penthouse at Tapestry On Central. North facing with possibly the best views in Midtown that include Camelback Mountain, Historic Willo and the Midtown/Uptown Phoenix skyline. Perfect for anyone who loves to entertain or cook will enjoy this completely custom and one of a kind kitchen unique to Tapestry. Features top of line appliances like Miele double ovens! Many other custom features like 8ft custom designer painted solid panel doors throughout. Enjoy sunsets and city views from the large roof top patios and decks. Don't forget about the convenience of the light rail stop just steps away. Just a few stops to restaurants, museums, arts and the downtown sports complex. Penthouse living just doesn't get better than this.

column9: What a find! A wonderfully maintained brick home on a picturesque corner lot in Willo, with a 2 car garage and a 2023 roof! Come live the charmed, historic neighborhood life, with gorgeous homes from the 20's-50's, fun neighborhood events, street fairs, and a general pride of ownership in this community full of Phoenix history. This home is move-in-ready with tile floors, shaker cabinetry, stainless steel appliances, indoor laundry with stackable washer/dryer, and even a Murphy bed in the guest room. Full bath with shower/tub combo in the hall for guests and an en-suite bathroom with walk in shower in the primary bedroom. The lot features a wonderful mature front yard on drip, and a rear yard with plenty of space complete w/ covered, paver-patio. Don't miss your chance to live in Willo!

column9: Rare find in Midtown Phoenix! This remodeled Tapestry On Central condo is move in ready. Located In the heart of Midtown you can sit on your patio or balcony and feel like you are in the midst of the historic Willo district. The interior features beautiful, upgraded flooring throughout. A beautiful porcelain chandelier, gorgeous fixtures & brushed gold hardware. Enjoy the upgraded chef's kitchen appliances and quartz counters. The laundry room off the kitchen has upgraded washer & dryer. There's even modern shutters throughout and your guest room/office is complete with a custom Murphy bed and private bath. Other great amenities are on site fitness center, heated pool & spa. On site Walgreens and Mary Coyle ice cream shop. A light rail stop is just steps away from your door. You can take the light rail to the many local restaurants, the arts district and sports complex. You can also take it right to Sky Harbor and not have to worry about parking. Don't miss this one! Remodeled units of this floorplan do not come up often.

column9: Rare end unit townhouse located in the heart of Midtown Phoenix, only one block away from Roosevelt Row! This modern, move-in ready home offers 3 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, a spacious great room with soaring ceilings, and a private patio with pavers and artifical grass. Minutes away, you'll find The Vig Fillmore, Cibo, Hance Park, the light rail, plus dozens of incredible restaurants, cocktail bars, breweries, and more! Whether you're a foodie, an art enthusiast, or simply seeking a vibrant city lifestyle, Midtown Phoenix has it all.

column9: Gorgeous 5th floor luxury condo at Tapestry on Central -- a gated community, close to downtown Phoenix. The complex sits across from The Heard Museum and a Phoenix light rail stop and is very close to the Phoenix Art Museum and great downtown restaurants and entertainment.

column9:
Completely Reimagined & Upgraded - This 1937 stunner has It All! 

Step into this exquisitely remodeled home where no detail was overlooked during a year-long renovation. Designed with intention and style, this property showcases vaulted ceilings, 9-ft interior doors, and custom slim shaker cabinetry throughout. The kitchen is a showstopper with luxurious leathered Taj Mahal quartzite countertops, high-end fixtures, and a layout perfect for entertaining. Enjoy the warmth of new hardwood floors, the elegance of marble tile, and the peace of mind that comes with new windows, plumbing, sewer lines, electrical, and roof. The primary suite is your private retreat, featuring a spa-style bathroom with separate soaking tub and shower, and a custom walk-in closet that feels like a boutique. Outside, enjoy the brand-new HEATED pool with in-ground cleaning system and a tranquil water feature perfect for Arizona living. The passthrough 2-car garage, surround sound, and thoughtful upgrades throughout add comfort and convenience. 

Need space for guests, hobbies, or a private studio? The attached guest house is fully equipped with its own kitchen and bathroom, ideal for visitors, a fitness room, or a creative workspace. This home is truly move-in ready with every detail already taken care of for you. Welcome to easy living with high design and top-tier finishes.

column9: UNICORN ALERT! Even by Willo Historic Neighborhood standards, this 'ol gal' is an elder! Built in 1929 and family owned since 1972, she has some stories to tell! Tucked on the last lot at the end of this beautiful street, there are several big remodels happening, creating new stories and occupants for the next chapter of the book. This Tudor revival has so many possibilities with its 2 bedrooms plus a bonus room in the back for an office/utility/3rd bedroom. Fabulous coved ceilings, gleaming original hardwood floors, even the fireplace will wink at you with a nod to yesteryear. Out back is a detached garage/storage and a custom metal cover for the perfect patio. Very private lot with space to create the perfect plan for your new home. Ones like this are rare, come catch this unicorn!

All within walking distance to local dining, the arts scene, and your favorite downtown spots!

column9: Step inside this gorgeous Downtown Townhome that offers privacy, greenery, and access to all the development going on downtown. A walkers paradise this 3 story townhome includes 2 bedrooms and 3 bathrooms, one on each floor. The ground floor includes a private, two car garage, almost unheard of downtown, a large family room/artists space that can be used as light commercial, tile throughout, a working fireplade and a half bath. Moving up to the second floor we have a newly remodeled modern kitchen with modern tile quartz counter tops with waterfall edge, shaker cabinets, tile backsplash and breakfast bar. Upgraded appliances include Viking Luxury refrigerator, dual wall mounted ovens with separate cooktop. and drawer mounted microwave. Also on this floor we have second family room area with tons of natural light and a fireplace, a private balcony overlooking 3rd Ave and a dining room area, also with a small balcony. Oak floors throughout these rooms. Moving up to the 3rd Floor 2 bedrooms with carpet for comfort, The primary bedroom has an en suite bath with stand up shower and separate tub, dual sinks and tile floors. Also includes a huge walk in closet and private balcony. Guest bedroom has tons of light from both east and west. 3rd Floor laundry is extra convenient. Ground floor of the unit can be used for light commercial or artist space. Absolutely one of the best locations in the valley if you want to live in the middle of the action. Portland Parkway park across the street. Japanese Friendship and Hance Park a block away. Saint Pasta, Fez, Valley Coffee Company, Fair Trade Coffee, First and Last, Pita Jungle and Match Market all within a block. Just a few blocks to Roosevelt Row, Protect bike lane into downtown and midtown, Light rail station two blocks away, freeway access to all destinations just a few blocks away as well. Walk Score of 86! that's as high as it gets in the Valley!

column9: Bring All Offers. Sellers Are Motivated and Very Negotiable. This is a rare opportunity to own a beautifully renovated historic home in the heart of the Willo Historic District. My clients are open, flexible, and ready to work with serious buyers. Welcome to the J and M Tharpe House, a 1919 Craftsman Bungalow filled with historic charm and modern designer updates. Located in one of Phoenix's most iconic neighborhoods, Willo is known for its architecture and close proximity to downtown arts, dining, and entertainment. Listed $100, 000 below comparable homes, this property is already priced to sell and the sellers are open to negotiation. In the past two years, the owners, including a well known interior designer, have completed extensive and thoughtful renovations to both the main house and guest house. Updates include full electrical upgrades with exterior 50 and 30 amp power, new dimmable lighting, smooth interior walls, popcorn ceiling removal, interior painting, and restored original woodwork. Additional improvements include a new roof, custom entry gates, updated fixtures and toilets, keypad locks, custom roller shades, and newer water heater, washer, dryer, dishwasher, and refrigerator. The Kool Deck has been refinished, and new mini split systems were added to both the guest house and laundry room. The exterior trim, eaves, and ceilings have also been painted. A vaulted wraparound porch sets a warm and welcoming tone. Inside, you'll find two bedrooms, two bathrooms, original hardwood and tile flooring, and a cozy wood burning fireplace. The spacious kitchen features stone countertops, a prep sink, recessed lighting, an authentic AGA stove, and French doors that open to a lush backyard retreat. Set on more than a quarter acre, the backyard is a true oasis with a sparkling pebble tec pool, mature fruit trees, lush landscaping, and a private courtyard. The property also includes a brick carriage house used as a workshop, a gated rear two car carport, and a front driveway that fits a 32 foot recreational vehicle plus two additional vehicles. The detached guest house is approximately 500 square feet and includes hardwood floors, a full kitchen with gas hook up, a fireplace, and a poolside patio. Both homes are currently leased to medical professionals at $2, 500 and $1, 800 per month, offering built-in income potential. Sellers are open to creative terms and flexible on timeline. Most indoor furniture and all outdoor furniture conveys with the property on a separate bill of sale.

Whether you're looking for a lock-and-leave lifestyle or a place to grow, this one checks every box!

column9: This exceptional home blends historic charm with modern efficiency. The limestone exterior offers durability and natural insulation, reducing energy costs, while the eco-friendly front yard boasts city views, H2O timers, and reclaimed materials throughout. The spacious backyard features lush grass, stone details, a bocce ball court and a quaint guest house complete with bathroom and kitchenette. AC and Roof are only 4 years old. Located in sought-after Willo District, this home offers unique design, smart upgrades, and unbeatable convenience. Also a cash flowing rental.

column9: Historic Charm meets modern flexibility in this incredibly loved and highly desired WILLO HOME. 1, 634 sf, 3BD/1BA, blends preserved character with fresh updates. The icing on the cake is a 441 sf detached structure in the southeast corner of the property offering endless potential for future use depending on needs/desires (guest house, studio, gym, ADU, or main house addition). Kitchen features new appliances, countertops, backsplash and laminate flooring. Freshly painted concrete floors, in beautiful condition, throughout the rest of the home and large laundry room. Functional & fluid Floor Plan, New Hot Water Heater. Nostalgia can be found in original cabinetry, telephone niche, bathroom, windows, 1940's sidewalk stamp and the nighttime twinkle of solar-lit front yard and backyard bistro lights. 7, 161 sf lot offers 2-car parking, private pool and north-south exposure. Just minutes from Encanto Park, golf (9 & 18 holes), Downtown, dining, St. Joseph's Hospital and Phoenix College. Find all the magic you're looking for in one of Phoenix's first historic suburbs, now offering all the amenities, culture and community! Please note detached Secondary Structure has ELECTRIC, no heating/cooling or plumbing.

column9: Discover the charm of urban living in the heart of Roosevelt Row, one of downtown Phoenix's most vibrant and eclectic neighborhoods. This 24-unit apartment complex, featuring a mix of 1-bedroom/1-bath units and studio apartments, offers tenants the perfect combination of comfort and convenience. With a total rentable square footage of 8, 788 SF, this property is just steps away from boutique restaurants, trendy bars, and unique shopping destinations. Each unit is individually metered for electricity, providing tenants with independent control over their utilities. The property also includes a community laundry room for added convenience. Currently, all units are occupied by an owner-user, and the owner may consider leasing back some units temporarily, depending on the terms. Please note that all numbers provided in the listing are proforma estimates. Located in the bustling Roosevelt Row area, this is a prime opportunity for investors seeking stable income and a property with excellent long-term potential. Please note: Drive-by only. Do not disturb tenants.

column9: The perfect mix of urban energy and single-family peace and quiet, this end-unit Roosevelt-area McKinley Row townhouse is the ideal home base to experience the incredible range of culinary and cultural activities Downtown Phoenix has to offer. Just steps from The Vig, Cibo Pizza, Lola Coffee, Proof Bread, First & Last, the Roosevelt/Central Light Rail station and the Japanese Garden, you can leave 2 cars charging in the 2-car attached garage and spend the weekends exploring, or sitting on the shady front porch watching the world go by. The first floor features the attached 2-car garage, and a roomy office space with views to the shady front porch and front yard. The second floor features the first of 2 HVAC zones (the first and second floor on zone 1), wood-look vinyl flooring, an oversized sun-filled kitchen with wrap-around bar seating, gas range with stainless hood, coffee station and quartz countertops; powder room, exposed-wood beams and a large living room leading to a spacious east-facing balcony with bar-seating and city lights views; the third floor features a second HVAC zone, stacked laundry station, plenty of storage, and 2 spacious en-suite bedrooms, the largest of which has soaring 15-foot ceilings, double-vanity, high-volume ceiling fan and 2-story corner windows with city-light views just over the tree canopy below. The attached 2-car garage features hanging storage racks and two 240V power outlets for easy EV charging (chargers not included). All windows/doors feature high-end roller sunshades, with blackout variants in each of the two bedrooms (the larger of the two bedrooms are also electric/remote-controlled). Entire community roof resealed as part of HOA-mandated maintenance in late 2023. Built in just 2018, and meticulously maintained by the original owners (and McKinley Row HOA Board member), this home offers all the peace of mind of a new build with the mature landscaping and quick-move-in of an established home.

column9: This charming 1942 ranch home with a modified English garden wall bond brick pattern, was designed by Jake Knapp and built by JR Womack in the heart of the Willo Historic District and located on one of its most sought-after streets. One thing you won't find in a home like this is a gigantic garage/workshop. If you are a car hobbyist, this may be the best deal downtown! Move in ready or ready for your personal aesthetic touches, this classic Willo home offers beautiful curb appeal and a traditional landscape that offers mature shade trees that leads you to the original front door and mailbox. As you enter, you'll discover gorgeous polished, integrally colored concrete floors, great trim work and large spacious rooms that are rare within this neighborhood. A huge front living room offers a great family comfort and a view to the front lawn. Corner windows in both the kitchen and living room offer a detail not seen in homes of this era. The kitchen has craftsman style oak cabinets and been beautifully remodeled to offer stone counters, excellent storage and direct access to the backyard. Windows have been replaced with dual pane insulated glass and home has been upgraded with newer gas fired furnaces and a gas fired tankless water heater. Charming historic details like the original milk bottle box by the back door where the homeowner could specify their order for the milkman to deliver. The backyard offers a nice blend of lawn and pavement for access to a gigantic, oversized air-conditioned and plumbed garage which could easily be transformed for a future casita with its own kitchen, bathroom, laundry or the added bonus of a detached office/studio. Perfect for working from home or creative endeavors. This home is perfect for urban living! As one of the first historic districts, Willo is only a breath away from the light rail, incredible dining, culture and all the amenities downtown Phoenix has to offer. It's not just a home but a piece of history ready to be cherished by its new owners. Embrace the blend of historical charm and modern convenience in this truly gorgeous landmark home. This lovely property is one not to miss. (Original 1942 blueprints of the home and detached conditioned space are available with the sale).

column9: Contemporary updates and timeless character in this stunning Willo District home. Set on a charming tree lined street, this 1936 gem has been fully transformed with premium finishes, designer touches, and restored historic details that honor its heritage. The bright and airy living spaces feature polished concrete floors, original wood elements, and a striking wood burning fireplace, while the remodeled kitchen offers stone countertops, stainless appliances and a fantastic pantry. The thoughtfully designed primary suite includes a luxurious custom shower and dual walk in closets, while the additional bedroom provides versatility for family, guests, or home office. Step outside through French doors into a private backyard oasis ready for year... round entertaining. The separate guest casita includes a full bedroom, bathroom, and kitchenette, creating an ideal setup for visitors or rental income. Major updates include a brand-new sewer system, and state-of-the-art water filtration, softener, and reverse osmosis systems for both the main home and casita. Nestled in the vibrant Willo Historic District, you'll enjoy walking distance to Midtown's best restaurants, shops, light rail, and cultural destinations. This home offers the rare opportunity to own a piece of Phoenix history reimagined for modern living.

column9: When Arizona achieved statehood, Roosevelt Historic District, the 'street car subdivision' was home to the Phoenix elite. Today it remains as ''Phoenix's finest example of residential preservation and architectural diversity.'' Tucked on a palm tree lined street, 525 W Portland is a rare opportunity to acquire the premier multi-family asset in this thriving arts district. Described in the National Register for Historic Places as 'a noteworthy example of a one-story Spanish Colonial Revival house' the property includes four distinct units, the centerpiece being a fully restored 1921 duplex. Behind that lives a charming 1930 1 bedroom house, a highly functional studio, and a two car garage. Three units will convey fully furnished for continued midterm or STR opportunity.

column9: Live an urban lifestyle in the Orpheum Lofts- the 2005 renovation of the historical landmark-Phoenix Title & Trust Building. Relax at the 2nd floor serene courtyard, containing shade structures, beautiful landscaping & lounging areas.

column9: How would you like to be the King of Phoenix? Available for the first time in 12 years: the Penthouse at Orpheum Lofts, which comes complete with the highest, private roof deck in the Valley! The key-locked elevator opens directly into the living room of the penthouse. Split bedroom layout with two split, rooftop terraces. Open kitchen with Wolf appliances. Indoor and outdoor fireplaces. Private trash chute. Projector in the living room. Valet parking and two storage units included. And more! Orpheum Lofts was originally built in 1931 as the Title and Trust building. Today, it's a full-service residential building with attended lobby, gym, pool, and multiple meeting rooms. Walking distance to Wren & Wolf, Suns and Diamondbacks arenas, & much more!

column9: Welcome to Willo!! Discover this enchanting 3 bedroom, 3 bathroom Bungalow in the Willo Historic District, a testament to architectural grace and modern comfort. Built by A L Johnson in 1925, this home spans a generous 2492 sf + a 664 square foot basement. The property also includes a detached two-car garage. The home's facade boasts classic design elements such as river rock porch details and decorative trim, meticulously preserved to honor its historical significance. Step inside to a world where heritage meets contemporary living, highlighted by a mix of newly refinished hardwood, tile, and carpet flooring that complements the abundance of natural light and exquisite details found throughout. A large front porch welcomes you, leading to a versatile flex roo ideal as a study or office adjacent to a formal living room with a striking brick fireplace. This opens to an elegant dining room adorned with stunning stained glass windows, creating a perfect backdrop for memorable gatherings. The kitchen is a chef's delight, equipped with stainless steel appliances and ample storage. The family room is bright and airy, fostering a perfect setting for relaxation or entertainment. Upstairs, the master suite is a retreat within itself, featuring a remarkable window and ceiling design, a custom-tiled bathroom with dual sinks, walk-in shower, standalone tub, and two closets. Two additional bedrooms and bathrooms offer spacious and beautifully detailed accommodations. The basement is an ideal space for a den, home theatre, or game room, offering additional flexible living space. This amazing home even has all new windows. Step outside to a backyard oasis complete with lush landscaping, a swimming pool, spa, and pergola perfect for enjoying the outdoors in privacy and style. As one of the first historic districts, Willo is steps away from the light rail, incredible dining, culture and amenities Phx offer. This home was featured in the Willo Historic District Home Tour of 2024. It is not just a residence but a piece of history ready to be cherished by its new owners. Embrace the blend of historical charm and modern convenience in this truly gorgeous landmark home.

column9: Welcome to your dream urban oasis! Nestled on the third floor of a modern condominium complex, this stunning 2-bedroom, 2-bathroom condo with a versatile den is a perfect blend of style, comfort, and convenience. Located just off Central Avenue, you'll find yourself in the heart of vibrant downtown Phoenix, where culture, entertainment, and lifestyle converge. The brand new carpet adds a touch of warmth, while freshly painted interiors create a clean, inviting atmosphere. The living area flows seamlessly into the dining space, making it ideal for entertaining friends or enjoying cozy nights in. The contemporary kitchen is a chef's delight, featuring sleek countertops, ample cabinetry, and modern appliances. Whether you're whipping up a gourmet meal or enjoying a quick breakfast, this space is designed for functionality and style. The condo boasts two spacious bedrooms, each offering plenty of closet space and large windows that frame views of the surrounding area. The master suite includes an en-suite bathroom for added privacy and convenience, while the second bedroom is perfect for guests, family, or as a home office. The den is a fantastic bonus! Living just off Central Avenue means you're steps away from some of Phoenix's most cherished attractions. Explore the vibrant arts scene at the Phoenix Art Museum or immerse yourself in the natural wonders at the Heard Museum. Sports enthusiasts will love being close to major sporting events, with venues like Chase Field and Footprint Center just a short drive away. Enjoy access to a range of community amenities, including a fitness center, swimming pool, and outdoor lounge areas.

Two parking spots and storage enhance convenience of city living at it's finest.

column9: One of the most extraordinary residences to become available at Portland Place. This corner home isn't just one of the most sought-after floorplans in the building; it's the only one of its kind. A sanctuary wrapped in light, texture, and intention, it spans the entire corner of the building, offering soul and substance you won't find anywhere else. Two expansive wraparound balconies, one overlooking the canopy of Portland Park, offering front-row views of the neighborhood's rhythm and charm. Floor-to-ceiling windows dissolve the boundary between indoors and out, inviting in sunrise light and Roosevelt Row energy. Inside, warmth and character unfold in layers, from the exposed block wall with a gas fireplace to the brick that carries through from the building's exterior, grounding the space with a sense of identity that only Portland Place offers. With just 54 residences, Portland Place is a true boutique community nestled in one of Downtown Phoenix's most vibrant, walkable, and culturally rich neighborhoods. Steps from Portland Park, the Japanese Friendship Garden, Roosevelt Row's galleries and murals, First Friday events, local coffee shops, and some of the city's most beloved restaurants- you're at the intersection of art, green space, and urban energy. Residents enjoy a rooftop pool with panoramic skyline views, secure access, and two underground garage parking spaces, offering the rare blend of privacy, convenience, and connection to the best of downtown living. This is Portland Place at its most iconic.

column9: Two Homes on One Lot. Welcome to 1018 S 4th Avenue, an Elegant, Rare opportunity. A Dual Home Oasis in the rapidly growing Central City South area of Phoenix. This unique R3 zoned property features two full-sized homes on one spacious lot, offering versatility, income potential, and proximity to everything the downtown core has to offer. As you step onto the property, you'll immediately appreciate the ample space, fresh renovations, and thoughtful interior and exterior layout that makes this dual residence ideal for owner-occupiers with rental income potential, multi-generational living, or investment purposes. The remodeled front home features a bright, open layout with four beds and two baths, while the two story rear house offers three separate bedrooms and a second ful Nestled on a spacious newly steel fenced & gated lot in the Flossmore neighborhood, this rare offering combines modern comforts, excellent rental income potential, and walkable access to Phoenix's top dining, culture, and sports venues. Perfect for investors, extended families, or savvy buyers seeking versatility. The Front House (Single-Story | 1, 829 SF) Beautifully remodeled with a clean, contemporary finish, this 4-bedroom, 2-bathroom home is move-in ready. The open-concept living area flows effortlessly into a modern kitchen featuring updated cabinetry, sleek countertops, and a large central island perfect for entertaining or family meals. The bedrooms are generously sized with plenty of natural light and closet space, while both bathrooms have been updated with modern fixtures and finishes. New flooring and fresh paint throughout create a light, airy ambiance. New package rooftop AC unit. Laundry hookups are located conveniently inside, and the front entrance has private fencing for added security and charm. The Rear House (Two-Story | 1, 800 SF) Tucked away in the back, the two-story home provides an ideal setup for a second family, long-term tenants, or even short-term rental guests. With 3 spacious bedrooms and 2 bathrooms, plus an upstairs loft area, this home offers flexibility for office space, a kids' play area, or an extended lounge. A full kitchen, separate laundry hookups, new package rooftop AC unit and private access make this a fully independent residencerarely found in central Phoenix. Just minutes from Downtown Phoenix, this property is in a high-demand urban neighborhood poised for growth. Walk or bike to ASU Downtown, Chase Field, Footprint Center, and the Roosevelt Row arts district. Quick access to the I-10 and I-17 freeways makes commuting easy, and Sky Harbor Airport is less than 15 minutes away. Whether you're an investor looking to capitalize on Phoenix's hot rental market or a homeowner wanting to live in one unit while renting the other, this is a prime location with unbeatable upside. Why 1018 S 4th Ave? Two complete homes on one lot - separately metered and self-sufficient Updated interiors with modern finishes No HOA - complete freedom for how you use the space Projected income potential: Live in one, rent the other for ~$2, 200-$2, 500/ month Future flexibility: Airbnb, long-term rental, or multi-generational use Zoned R-3 - Multifamily opportunity Nearby Amenities 2 minutes to Downtown Phoenix 3 blocks to public transportation 5 minutes to ASU, Valley Metro Rail Close to coffee shops, grocery stores, and schools The Bottom Line This is a rare finda multi-unit property in one of Phoenix's most strategic and fastest-developing areas. Whether you're a savvy investor or a homeowner who wants flexibility and rental income, 1018 S 4th Ave is a must-see.

column9: Elegant modern living with stunning uptown and mountain views in a prime Midtown Phoenix location. Discover this stunning residence featuring exquisite custom flooring throughout. As you enter, be greeted by a beautiful mosaic floor tile medallion and an art glass wall that elegantly divides the entry from the kitchen. The home has soaring 10-foot ceilings in the main living areas and bedrooms and radiates spaciousness and elegance. The chef's kitchen has been beautifully remodeled, showcasing top-of-the-line Monogram appliances, including a 36-inch induction cooktop and an undercounter wine cooler, all set against stylish cabinetry and sleek countertops. This culinary dream is designed for both functionality and aesthetics. The home features two large primary suites, each with its own bathroom and walk-in closet, providing an ideal retreat for relaxation. In addition, there's a large versatile office that can easily serve as an third bedroom, along with a convenient half bath for guests. The east primary ensuite has also undergone a stunning remodel, featuring modern fixtures and finishes that create a luxurious atmosphere. In addition, it boasts a massive walk-in closet, providing ample space for all your wardrobe needs and ensuring easy organization. Enjoy energy-efficient living with new LED lighting and wall switches throughout, alongside accent lighting atop kitchen cabinets and in the entry and master bedroom ceilings. The home features new contemporary 8-foot interior wood doors and a new ceiling soffit designed in the central living area, enhancing the overall aesthetic. The large laundry-storage room comes with built-in cabinets and two additional storage closets, providing ample space for organization. The main living area and both bedroom suites are wired for sound with volume control, ready for your audio enjoyment. Custom blackout shades behind window shades in both bedroom suites ensure restful nights, while the new paint throughout adds a fresh and modern touch. Enjoy cozy evenings by the gas fireplace, and view the twinkling city lights at the same time. This home also offers two side-by-side parking spaces in the underground garage and two large covered terraces, perfect for outdoor relaxation. Facing north, this residence enjoys low HVAC expenses. There is even an onsite nail salon and pharmacy for added convenience too. Don't miss the opportunity to make this luxurious property your new home!

column9: This Home has a story A charming 1917 Craftsman Home in the Evans Churchill District just steps from the heart of Roosevelt Row, one of the last original residences in the area. Welcome to opportunity with Versatile City-zoning for mixed use - This property offers incredible flexibility whether you envision creating your Urban dream residence, a trendy restaurant, a retail business or other venture, the use permit offers great flexibility for an unparalleled opportunity in one of Phoenix's most sought-after neighborhoods. You'll be at the center of Phoenix's First Friday Art Walk creating a lively cultural experience. Surrounded by exciting new eclectic dining options, galleries and shopping, you'll never run out of places to explore. Plus, you're just a stone's throw away from ASU's downtown campus, easy freeway access, major sporting events, concerts, and endless dining options. Don't miss out on this rare opportunity to own a piece of Phoenix history in a location that has it all - uncover the endless possibilities this property has to offer!

column9: READY for your next move? Look no further! This popular upgraded condominium is centrally located near the heart of downtown Phoenix. Close to shopping, restaurants, coffee shops, museums, the Valley Metro rail system and much more. Discover what this 3-level modern home has to offer including 2-bedrooms, 2-bathrooms, 2 living spaces with a versatile design on 2 separate floors, and a 1.5-car garage. Explore the industrial loft design with high wood & corrugated metal ceilings, a neutral palette, large windows on each floor, accented with nice brick walls, and polished concrete floors throughout the main living spaces on the first & second floors, and a well-designed patio, perfect for enjoying a morning cup of coffee. The large primary bedroom features soft carpeting, a contemporary wooden closet, and an ensuite bathroom with a tile shower from floor to ceiling, and a single vanity. The additional bedroom also features soft carpeting with a private bathroom. Don't miss the stacked laundry area located on the first floor under the stairs and the amazing city views from every window! Fully fenced backyard patio is ideal for relaxing. Move-in-ready!! Upgrades/features list available upon request. HVAC installed (2023). Hot water heater installed (2023). Water purifier and drinking system available.

column9: This modern condo offers the perfect combination of comfort and convenience in the heart of downtown. With its prime location across from the highly sought-after Margaret T. Hance Park, this unit presents an incredible opportunity for urban living at its finest. The unit is in the building's preferred setting, just a couple doors from the main staircase and elevator. Upon entering, you will be greeted by an inviting and open floor plan that seamlessly integrates the living, dining, and kitchen areas. With ample natural light streaming through nice, large windows, it creates a warm and inviting ambiance. It's the perfect space for relaxation or entertaining guests. The kitchen is a chef's dream, featuring matching cool, retro-feel appliances, sleek quartz countertops, and abundant storage in beautifully enameled cabinets and pantry. Whether you're hosting a dinner party or preparing a quick meal, this kitchen is sure to please the pickiest buyer! The bedrooms offer comfortable living space and plenty of room for personalization. The bathrooms are elegantly designed with contemporary fixtures and finishes, providing a spa-like experience. Residents will also have access to a range of desirable amenities. These include a generous sparkling pool heated in winter months, communal gathering spaces with BBQ grill, a welcoming open lobby with zen fountain atmosphere, and a gated/covered parking area, ensuring that every aspect of your lifestyle is catered to. Situated in the heart of the vibrant art and culture of Roosevelt Row & Arts District, this condo offers walking-distance access to a myriad of dining, shopping, and entertainment options. From trendy restaurants and cozy cafs to art galleries and boutiques, you'll find everything you need just steps away from your front door. The unit's location also allows for convenient closeness to Arizona State University's Downtown Campus, Convention Center and professional sports arenas. Don't miss the opportunity to own this remarkable unit in a prime location. Come experience the epitome of modern urban living!

column9: Located in Ashland Place historic district, this 1920 Spanish Revival home has all the charm you are looking for. Located in the Midtown Arts District within walking distance to the light rail, Heard Museum, Phoenix Theater, restaurants and more.

The split floor plan offers a spacious primary retreat with walk-in closet, extra large soaking tub and double vanity sinks. It even has access to the large balcony. There is even a Walgreen's pharmacy on the first floor along with a nail salon. So many conveniences come with this home!

column9: Step into a piece of history with this charming 2-bedroom, 2-bathroom home, a relic of Phoenix's pioneering co-operative living era, built in 1957 by Del Webb Corp. Designed by architect Ralph C. Harris, this Mid-Century Modern marvel boasts iconic stacked ranch-style homes across 14 floors, totaling 60 units. Situated in Midtown Phoenix, adjacent to the Heard Museum and just north of the Phoenix Art Museum, residents enjoy unparalleled cultural immersion. Each unit features spacious balconies adorned with concrete ledges and fins, offering shade and serenity amidst the vibrant cityscape, epitomizing timeless elegance and urban sophistication.

column9: WELCOME HOME to this unique historic property with TWO HOUSES! Enjoy city views in almost every direction from this customized historic property located in the Ashland Place Historic District within walking distance to the light rail, restaurants, museums and the theatre. Inside, you'll find 3 beds/2 baths with charming archways, tall ceilings and exposed beams in the kitchen. The home has been remodeled to enhance the home's original details with the perfect balance of modern design offering quartz counters, custom cabinetry, beautiful herringbone tilework, and designer fixtures throughout. Fantastic upgrades make this feel like a new home! Outside you'll enjoy a huge backyard, large pergola patio, an outdoor kitchen and a complete 1 bed/1 bath guest house!

column9: Downtown living, one block from Roosevelt Row! This well-appointed 2 bedroom, 2 bath at en Hance Park Condominiums is located on the highly sought after 4th floor, w/eastern orientation offering mountain and city views from every window. The community is of newer construction, built in 2017. Residence features a split floor plan with two bedroom en suites, each with a walk in closet. The upgraded kitchen boasts quartz countertops, stainless appliances, and an abundance of storage, including a pantry. LVT flooring in the living areas and 10'8'' ceilings create an open, yet inviting environment. Spacious bathrooms each have an oversized shower with glass enclosure and tile surround. Water softener and new paint! Walkable, gated community, with pool, secured parking, elevator to all floors. The community is located across from Margaret T. Hance Park and one block from Roosevelt Row offering an abundance of festivals, concerts, sporting events and the monthly First Friday Art Festival. One block from light rail with easy access to freeways and airport. This pet-friendly community has a healthy HOA which includes water, sewer, trash, building maintenance, insurance and covered, secured parking.

column9: Rare opportunity to live in a secluded gated community in the heart of Phoenix with a private garage providing direct access to this fully renovated 2 bed, 2 bath unit. Vaulted ceilings create ample natural lighting throughout. All appliances, flooring, carpet, paint and fixtures completely redone in 2017. Garage has clean epoxy floors and several storage racks for all your needs. The upstairs primary bedroom includes large closet, walk in double head shower, and dual vanities. Unit comes furnished with all the furniture/decor/tv's shown in photos. Additional AC unit in master to make it super cold during summer. Owners get access to the community parking lot, clubhouse, jacuzzi, heated pool and grills. HOA fees include water/sewage/trash. HOA replaced roof & repainted exterior in 2020 In this complex of 60 units, only 24 are three stories high, and just 12 have this specific floor plan. Community located directly across from ASU, UA, and is walking distance to all the new restaurants, bars, coffee shops, sports stadiums, farmer's markets, Roosevelt Row, and First Fridays. This location makes this an incredible investment opportunity.

column9: Refreshed with ivory satin paint throughout, along with updated light switches and grounded outlets, this classically beautiful residence awaits you in the iconic Phoenix Towers. Grand-sized rooms with higher ceilings and expansive picture windows define the living spaces, complemented by a spacious balcony, all on the cooler and quieter side of the building. The rooftop terrace offers breathtaking city lights and mountain views, providing an exquisite backdrop for your gatherings. Enjoy resort-style living with a heated saltwater lap pool, complete with a kitchen and barbecue area. Nearby Encanto/Central light rail station affords easy access to downtown, the airport, and ASU. The all inclusive cooperative monthly covers taxes, utilities, maintenance, management, and broadband Internet. The 24/7 door staff ensures security. Two assigned underground parking spaces and a dedicated storage area enhance convenience. Amenities include an exercise room, a fenced dog park and an organic community garden. Timeless design and beauty draw the eye and touch with louvered doors; hardwood for sills, master suite armoire, and the open sided art display shelving between the great room and hallway; as well as a sparkling mirrored mini-bar with illuminated glass shelving. Kitchen has classic Beauty Queen steel cabinetry, a vintage lovers' favorite. Superior building craft of the MCM era is evident with quiet concrete construction; interior walls made of 1 plaster over metal lath and mesh; and fully enclosed wiring. Powerful central plant cooling and heating system, with four vertical stack mains, delivers both cooling and heating modes year round. Building has modernized with dual pane windows, electronic access control and a multi-camera security system.

column9: 20th Floor, largest unit with 360 degree STUNNING views, which are showcased by the floor-to-ceiling windows throughout, with each and every single room opening to balconies. The balconies, by the way? Are unlike any you've seen before, and truly extend your living space. Dining al fresco can't be beat! But we are getting ahead of ourselves, and when you see the inside of this luxury condo? You may never want to venture outside! Recently remodeled top-to-bottom with Brazilian wood floors throughout, the ceilings have all been taken up and are accented thanks to the hand-picked lighting throughout. The crown moulding and 6'' custom baseboards show an attention to craftsmanship you haven't seen before. The primary bedroom features a walk-in custom closet, separate shoe closet (cont and the primary bath features luxury touches as well. Take, for instance, the deep, jetted soaking tub and heated towel rack that rival any spa! The guest bedroom is equally impressive, featuring a large walk-in closet, an oversized, walk-in shower and so much more. We'd be remiss if we forgot to mention the great room, which is truly great in every way; and the dining room allows for intimate dinners --or grand gatherings. The kitchen is a chef's delight and offers the opportunity for easy, breezy breakfasts, or use it as the current owners do: A secondary seating area and more intimate entertaining area. There's also a wonderful reading nook and office area accented by a beautiful bookcase, and if this sounds like a home like no other, it's because, quite frankly, it is! Even the laundry room is impressive! (seriously, it's a cool room! Look up when you get inside!). It's also in a building like no other: A true lock-and-leave, the ROC features amenities galore, including a heated pool, spa, cabanas and entertaining area including a super cool MCM fire pit surrounded by jasmine and green space. The gym was recently renovated, with top-of-the-line, iFit-enabled machines throughout, and the ROC Room? Is the perfect place to hang with the neighbors--or host your next event. 24-hour a day, 7 day a week door personnel, underground parking, and individual storage units come with each home, and many of the staff have been here for years--for a reason! Even the pups are treated like royalty, and yes, that IS a private dog Pup Park! Truly magnificent, come make 2001 your next home!

column9: One of the most beautiful Historic properties in Phoenix! Built in 1927 in the Los Olivos Community, a Historic Neighborhood adjacent to the Arts District developed by Dwight B Heard, this iconic Storybook Tudor is always showcased when researching historic homes in Phoenix. With its dramatic Tudor architecture and expansive 3/4 acre property, the curb appeal alone takes you back in time! The current owner has meticulously retained all the historical charm and elegance while updating and improving the property. Elegant community rooms with soaring wood beamed ceilings, artfully crafted solid Mahogany doors and paneling, paned windows, Italian cornices and draperies, Steuben and other antique chandeliers. From the foyer is the dramatic staircase with its original Terrazzo floors. Beautiful Chef's kitchen with island, Subzero and Miele appliances. Laundry Room with antique cast iron sink. 3 bedrooms upstairs including the large Primary Bedroom with William Morris draperies. Primary Bath with original and preserved Green Ceramic Tile. Charming Guest Bath with Dormered Ceilings. Detached Coach House (Garage) with Guest House offering a full bath, loft bedroom, and kitchenette. Backyard Oasis with long rectangular pool, flanked by Italian Cypresses and featuring an imported English water feature. Beautiful Gazebo with commercial grade mist system for year round enjoyment. Large AC cooled Chicken Coop and orchard sporting over 15 fruit trees conveys unrivaled rural living in the center of the city. Make this iconic historical home located in the heart of the city yours to showcase!
column11: 363 E Monte Vista Rd, Phoenix, AZ, 85004

column9: WOW, LOOK AT THAT PRICE! VIEWS, VIEWS, VIEWS! Welcome to urban luxury living at its finest! This beautifully maintained 2-bedroom, 2-bathroom penthouse boasts a harmonious blend of modern design and contemporary comfort. Only two lofts in the middle with the BEST west facing views... Imagine those Arizona sunsets! Step inside and be greeted by the spacious open floor plan, adorned with natural light pouring in from the expansive windows, offering panoramic views of the vibrant cityscape. Gorgeous laminate flooring sweeps through the lower level with luxury vinyl upstairs. The well-appointed kitchen is a culinary enthusiast's dream, featuring sleek granite countertops, modern black appliances, and ample storage space. The upstairs primary bedroom is a serene retreat complete with a lavish ensuite bathroom featuring dual sinks, a large shower, and a spa-like soaking tub, perfect for unwinding after a long day. Take advantage of all FOUR closet spaces upstairs! The second bedroom and bathroom offers versatility and comfort for guests or family members. Step outside your sliding glass door and onto your private patios. Take a look at those VIEWS! Grab a cup of coffee and enjoy the beautiful sunrise, or unwind after a long day of work by enjoying a gorgeous Arizona sunset overlooking the pool! Whether you're looking for a shaded hide out on the lower level, or looking to bask in the sun, both patios are spacious, private and relaxing! This loft is set up perfectly for those who work from home, those who need quick access to public transportation or those looking for highly walkable areas! Residents of the Tapestry on Central can enjoy access to an array of luxurious amenities, including a state-of-the-art fitness center, a relaxing pool and spa, a community theater and MORE! The Tapestry also features ground level shops including a Walgreens pharmacy, a secured entrance and secure underground parking - what more could you ask for?! This unit has been allocated two of the BEST oversized parking spots near the elevators with nobody parking next to you (#1062 and #1063). Conveniently situated in the heart of Phoenix, this residence provides easy access to a multitude of dining, shopping, and entertainment options, ensuring a lifestyle of convenience and leisure. Located just minutes from the new downtown Creighton Medical School and more! Step outside The Tapestry and enjoy quick access to the light rail or take a stroll to the nearby amenities! Don't miss the opportunity to experience the epitome of sophisticated urban living!

column9: Be prepared to fall in love with this beautifully updated 1915 bungalow situated on a spectacular Estate sized 3/4 acre lush irrigated lot in the historic LOS OLIVOS district. Built when architecture was an art form & maintained & updated with style & elegance. Take your morning coffee in the exquisite breakfast room or just through those french doors on the amazing back patio both with views sure to impress. The kitchen features Viking & Sub-Zero appliances.The primary suite includes heated bathroom floors, jetted tub & steam shower.Custom stained original wood floors. Updates include : restored windows, HVAC system, plumbing, tankless water heater, electrical, newly built Casita with Wolf range & Bosch appliances, vaulted ceilings & polished concrete floors. Detached garage w/ gated drive. Square footage includes the basement , main house & Casita. Did somebody say WINE CELLAR ? The basement would be a fantastic place for your vino! Oh and want to expand into the attic? Use your imagination & ask your contractor what that space could accommodate. CLOSE TO : Phoenix Art Museum, Heard Museum, Arizona Science Center, Chase Field Baseball Stadium, Footprint Center (basketball, hockey & indoor football stadium) Orpheum Theatre, Herberger Theatre, Roosevelt Row Cultural District, Grand Ave Cultural District, Phoenix Theatre company, Ballet Arizona, The Phoenix Symphony, Various Restaurants : including Chef Chris Bianco's world famous Italian. SHOP AT NEARBY : Biltmore Fashion Park, Uptown Plaza.Park Central, local artisan shops, Town and Country shopping Center, Scottsdale Fashion Square.GOLF AT NEARBY: Arizona Biltmore Golf Club, Encanto Golf Resort, Phoenix Country Club. ASU, NAU and UofA all have major campuses in nearby downtown Phoenix. Located near major medical facilities & transportation arteries -Light Rail , Sky Harbor Airport, I-10 Freeway , Hwy 51. PARKS & NATURAL ATTRACTIONS: Margaret Hance Park, Encanto Park, Phoenix Country Club, North Mountain Preserve, Camelback Mountain, Piestewa Peak, & South Mountain. THE PERFECT HOME & just minutes away from it ALL ! What more can one ask for?

column9: Welcome to a rare gem in the heart of Phoenix! This exceptional end unit Brownstone-style home is a true standout, boasting an abundance of natural light and unique features. Upon entering the private gated entry, you'll appreciate the convenience of an attached garage, along with the luxury of an in-unit elevator for easy access to all five floors. The home offers a spacious and thoughtfully designed layout, featuring three bedrooms and an impressive 5.5 bathrooms. The large master suite is a sanctuary of relaxation and comfort. A key highlight of this property is the incredible rooftop deck and several balconies that provide stunning views Phoenix as well as open air. This home has been meticulously cared for, with recent updates including new carpet and fresh paint in most of the home. column9: Rare opportunity to experience Phoenix living at St. Croix Villas Condominiums! Pride of ownership shows in this beautifully maintained 2 bed, 2 bath townhome. Huge windows combined w/ vaulted ceilings create ample natural lighting throughout! The updated eat-in kitchen showcases brand new floating shelves, breakfast bar, white cabinets, granite countertops, stainless steel appliances, & pantry. Down the hallway you will find Bedroom2 & full bathroom. The freshly coated spiral staircase leads to your attached private garage w/ direct access to the home. The upstairs primary bedroom includes large closet, walk in shower, dual vanities, & laundry. Just outside the primary you will find a nook perfect for office space! AC is brand new as of 2021 & accessible windows replaced! This amazing condo is close to ASU phx campus, the Phx Convention Center, public transit services, a variety of restaurants, grocery stores, convenience stores, & so much more! Easy access to the I-10 freeway. St Croix includes a community heated pool & spa, gated entrance & parking, & community center, Roof & exterior maintenance provided by the HOA. HOA fees include water/sewage/trash

column9: Welcome to Summit at Copper Square! This luxury high-rise building provides low-maintenance urban lifestyle living w/ beautiful community spaces right in the heart of Downtown Phoenix. Residence #1710 offers an extended corner balcony with 180-degree, unobstructed views including South Mountain & Chase Field. With a split floor plan including a Den that works perfectly for an at-home office, a full-size washer & dryer, & a fabulous full-size parking space, this condo will feel like home instantly! Walking distance from Chase Field, the Footprint Center & all the great downtown restaurants!

column9: UNICORN ALERT! Feel the pitter patter of your heartbeat as you walk into this amazing penthouse loft and see the eye candy views this home offers! You cannot help but be drawn to the windows to check out Hance Park, the downtown skyline and the urban life below. In case you need the view AND fresh air, head right up to the private rooftop deck and take it all in, you will not be disappointed! Inside boasts almost 3100 sq feet of pure urban loft bliss with 20 foot ceilings, exposed ductwork, metal staircases and steel braided railings. The primary bedroom is 1st floor with a walk in closet, fantastic bath and lots of light and storage. A NYC styled kitchen open to the whole area is perfect for entertaining. Upstairs is 2 more areas for guests, lounge or more. Perfect location, outstanding building so close to the light rail, art museum, the opera, restaurants and more. Close to downtown, but not in the tight mix of downtown. All the perks and views, none of the hustle! Artisan Lofts on Central has a huge lap pool, spa, dog run and each unit has 2 parking spaces with electrical charging available. Backing to the Roosevelt historic district, it is perfect for those who yearn for a urban life and love the quiet stroll thru a charming historic neighborhood. Come check this loft out, it will amaze you as it has the rest of us!

column9: A rare opportunity to own in Arizona's most historic residential high-rise buildings, Phoenix Towers. This true modern home has been meticulously cared for preserving the integrity of the original 1957 details. This mid-century Co-Op is a modern lover's dream featuring numerous original finishes appliances in pristine condition, from the pressed aluminum kitchen cabinetry to the original Hotpoint appliances. Spacious rooms offer comfortable living with large windows overlooking the pool and Phoenix Heard Museum. Residents also enjoy the best view in town from the panoramic roof-top terrace, community garden, dog park, and resort-sized lap pool.

column9: This exceptional development opportunity blends historical preservation with modern potential. column9: Come fall in love. Here's a rare opportunity to own a stylish multi-level home with a sought after location & awesome daytime and night time views. I interviewed the neighbors; they love living there. 1st level is the foyer and garage. 2nd level is the south facing great room, north facing kitchen, and powder room. 3rd level has 2 bedrooms and 2 baths and a built-in washer-dryer. 4th level is the penthouse styled master bedroom with south facing balcony overlooking downtown Phoenix's iconic landmarks. The master bedroom features a walk-in closet and its own 3/4 bath with double sinks & commode with privacy. If you appreciate good architecture, and don't mind staircases, this is the right place for you. If you own 2 cars, there's plenty of room to park in the tandem style deep garage.

column9: UNBEATABLE LOCATION URBAN LIVING ENDLESS AMENITIES Discover the best of downtown Phoenix living in this stunning 3-bedroom, 3.5-bath tri-level condo with an attached 2-car garage and extra storage. Just steps from the light rail on Central Avenue, Margaret T. Hance Park, Roosevelt Row, top dining, nightlife, art museums, and the Phoenix Theater Companyyou'll be immersed in the city's energy with everything at your fingertips. Step through the gated courtyard into a bright and airy home featuring a neutral palette, brand-new carpet, and upgrades including a new AC unit, water softener, and reverse osmosis system. The first level offers a flexible bonus room and half bathperfect for an office, gym, or guest suite. The second level is where life happens, with an open-concept kitchen that flows into a spacious great room filled with natural light. Step onto your private balcony to enjoy the views overlooking the community pool, spa, and landscaped courtyard. On the top floor, you'll find three bedrooms, two baths, and a conveniently located laundry area. From morning coffee on the balcony to evenings exploring Roosevelt Row, this home offers a lifestyle that blends privacy, convenience, and urban vibrancy. This is the opportunity to enjoy downtown living at its finest. Scheduleyour showing today!

column9: Pristine Penthouse in the heart of Midtown Phoenix art district. Perched atop the historical Regency House on the 22nd floor, this contemporary, luxurious home offers urban living at its finest. Both north-facing covered balconies offer 180-degree views of Camelback Mountain. Piestewa Peak, Four Peaks and the Central Uptown Phoenix skyscape. Stunning open floor plan with high concrete ceilings accented with cable lighting, and motorized shades over upgraded floor to ceiling dual paned low-e windows. Chef's kitchen and bathrooms offer custom designed cabinetry and satin finish granite counter tops. Primary and guest bedroom closets, laundry, pantry and front closets all designed by California Closets. HOA provides 24-hour concierge, air conditioning and heat, water, personal storage unit, assigned parking, heated community pool and spa, gym, BBQ and stylish gathering areas. Walking distance to the Heard Museum, the Phoenix Art Museum, restaurants, shops and nightlife. Dog-walking friendly historical home district with quaint neighborhoods surround the area. Steps away to the light rail, which can be taken directly to Sky Harbor Airport and various sporting and cultural events. This home is turn-key, and suitable as a perfect lock and leave luxury primary residence, Corporate Retreat, or investment property. Some custom furnishings convey. Agent is related to owner.

column9: A rare chance to own a fully modernized piece of true Phoenix and Arizona history. Built in 1915 for Parker L. Woodman, mining superintendent of the Copper Queen Mine in Bisbee (one of the largest in the world at that time), this Neo-Colonial home originally stood along Central Avenue at 11 E. Ashland. After serving as an art gallery for 18 years starting in mid-80's, it became the last remaining residential building on Central between McDowell and Thomas. With development approaching, it was saved from demolition and moved (by city permit) to Lynwood Street in 2006. As a condition of the move, all major systems were brought to code - new foundation, plumbing, sewer, electrical, roof, and split HVAC. What remains original are the historic details that matter - coffered ten-foot ceilings, rich fir floors, five-panel doors, painted cast stone masonry with full slab fireplace mantel, multi-light windows, and a classic Palladian gable. Currently setup as 5-8 offices (depending on configuration), some are large enough to be a conference room. Full bathroom downstairs, and a half bath up and down. Kitchen and dining room on the first floor. Zoned DTC-EEVER (Downtown Code - East Evergreen), the property offers rare live/work flexibility. It's ideally suited for office use - law, architecture, design, wellness, or consulting - or for creative studio space, gallery, or boutique retail. The zoning also permits full residential use or a combination of both. Whether you need a client-facing space with character, a quiet retreat for focused work, or a one-of-a-kind live/work hybrid, this property can adapt to your vision while maintaining its historic charm. Eight off-street parking spaces are included, along with a recorded ingress/egress easement to the west. Opportunities like this - where character, location, and zoning align - don't come around often.

The kitchen has been updated and remodeled and ready for its new owner. Expansive views with amazing sunsets. The summit has 24/7 front desk concierge, work out facility, swimming pool and bbq. The lobby has been recently remodeled along with new carpet and paint on all the floors (2025) Cherry wood flooring, stainless steel appliances with updated LED lighting. Check it out and enjoy life at the Summit!

column9: Enjoy the experience of downtown condo living at Summit at Copper Square! Located on the 9th floor w/ breathtaking views of the city & mountains with a wrap around private balcony. Contemporary interior design featuring beautiful hardwood floors, floor to ceiling windows from living areas & both bedrooms provide lots of natural light. Spacious designer kitchen w/ granite counters, dining area, SS appliances, & wood cabinetry. Upscale baths offer granite & Corian counters, designer tile & fixtures. Generous sized bedrooms w/ walk-in closets. Lots of storage. This unit includes 2 indoor gated garage parking spots, 1 spot + lift. HOA includes WiFi, water, gas, sewer & garbage. Luxurious/high end amenities include 24 hour security, heated negative-edge pool, spa, sauna, state of the art exercise room open 24/7, meeting/lounge area, as well as a rooftop terrace clubhouse with firepit! A portion of the monthly HOA fee goes towards replacement of equipment as required. Across the street from Diamondbacks baseball stadium (Chase Field). 3 min walk to the light rail. 5 min walk to Phoenix Suns basketball arena (Footprint Center). 5 min drive to Sky Harbor Airport. Dozens of bars, restaurants, comedy club, convention center, other miscellaneous shops within a 10 minute walk. Mountain views South and West, perfect view of beautiful sunsets nightly.
